ctl_bw.name: ctl_bw
ctl_bw.long_desc: Speed controller bandwidth, in Hz. Higher values result in faster speed and current rise times, but may result in overshoot and higher current consumption. For fixed-wing aircraft, this value should be less than 50 Hz; for multirotors, values up to 100 Hz may provide improvements in responsiveness.

ctl_dir.name: ctl_dir
ctl_dir.long_desc: Motor spin direction as detected during initial enumeration. Use 0 or 1 to reverse direction.

ctl_gain.name: ctl_gain
ctl_gain.long_desc:
Speed (RPM) controller gain. Determines controller
            aggressiveness; units are amp-seconds per radian. Systems with
            higher rotational inertia (large props) will need gain increased;
            systems with low rotational inertia (small props) may need gain
            decreased. Higher values result in faster response, but may result
            in oscillation and excessive overshoot. Lower values result in a
            slower, smoother response.

esc_index.name: esc_index
esc_index.short_desc: Index of this ESC in throttle command messages.
esc_index.long_desc: Index of this ESC in throttle command messages.

mot_i_max.name: mot_i_max
mot_i_max.long_desc:
Motor current limit in amps. This determines the maximum
            current controller setpoint, as well as the maximum allowable
            current setpoint slew rate. This value should generally be set to
            the continuous current rating listed in the motor’s specification
            sheet, or set equal to the motor’s specified continuous power
            divided by the motor voltage limit.

mot_kv.name: mot_kv
mot_kv.short_desc: Motor Kv in RPM per volt
mot_kv.long_desc:
Motor Kv in RPM per volt. This can be taken from the motor’s
            specification sheet; accuracy will help control performance but
            some deviation from the specified value is acceptable.

mot_ls.name: mot_ls
mot_ls.short_desc: READ ONLY: Motor inductance in henries.
mot_ls.long_desc: READ ONLY: Motor inductance in henries. This is measured on start-up.

mot_num_poles.name: mot_num_poles
mot_num_poles.long_desc:
Number of motor poles. Used to convert mechanical speeds to
            electrical speeds. This number should be taken from the motor’s
            specification sheet.

mot_rs.name: mot_rs
mot_rs.short_desc: READ ONLY: Motor resistance in ohms
mot_rs.long_desc:
READ ONLY: Motor resistance in ohms. This is measured on start-up. When
            tuning a new motor, check that this value is approximately equal
            to the value shown in the motor’s specification sheet.

mot_v_max.name: mot_v_max
mot_v_max.long_desc:
Motor voltage limit in volts. The current controller’s
            commanded voltage will never exceed this value. Note that this may
            safely be above the nominal voltage of the motor; to determine the
            actual motor voltage limit, divide the motor’s rated power by the
            motor current limit.

gnss.warn_dimens.name: gnss.warn_dimens
gnss.warn_dimens.long_desc:
Set the device health to Warning if the dimensionality of
              the GNSS solution is less than this value. 3 for the full (3D)
              solution, 2 for planar (2D) solution, 1 for time-only solution,

GPS_DUMP_COMM.long_desc: If this is set to 1, all GPS communication data will be published via uORB, and written to the log file as gps_dump message.  If this is set to 2, the main GPS is configured to output RTCM data, which is then logged as gps_dump and can be used for PPK.

GPS_UBX_DYNMODEL.long_desc: u-blox receivers support different dynamic platform models to adjust the navigation engine to the expected application environment.

GPS_SAT_INFO.name: GPS_SAT_INFO
GPS_SAT_INFO.long_desc: Enable publication of satellite info (ORB_ID(satellite_info)) if possible. Not available on MTK.

GPS_UBX_MODE.name: GPS_UBX_MODE
GPS_UBX_MODE.long_desc: Select the u-blox configuration setup. Most setups will use the default, including RTK and dual GPS without heading.  If rover has RTCM corrections from a static base (or other static correction source) coming in on UART2, then select Mode 5. The Heading mode requires 2 F9P devices to be attached. The main GPS will act as rover and output heading information, whereas the secondary will act as moving base. Modes 1 and 2 require each F9P UART1 to be connected to the Autopilot. In addition, UART2 on the F9P units are connected to each other. Modes 3 and 4 only require UART1 on each F9P connected to the Autopilot or Can Node. UART RX DMA is required. RTK is still possible with this setup.

GPS_UBX_BAUD2.name: GPS_UBX_BAUD2
GPS_UBX_BAUD2.long_desc: Select a baudrate for the F9P's UART2 port. In GPS_UBX_MODE 1, 2, and 3, the F9P's UART2 port is configured to send/receive RTCM corrections. Set this to 57600 if you want to attach a telemetry radio on UART2.

GPS_YAW_OFFSET.name: GPS_YAW_OFFSET
GPS_YAW_OFFSET.short_desc: Heading/Yaw offset for dual antenna GPS
GPS_YAW_OFFSET.long_desc: Heading offset angle for dual antenna GPS setups that support heading estimation.  Set this to 0 if the antennas are parallel to the forward-facing direction of the vehicle and the rover (or Unicore primary) antenna is in front.  The offset angle increases clockwise.  Set this to 90 if the rover (or Unicore primary, or Septentrio Mosaic Aux) antenna is placed on the right side of the vehicle and the moving base antenna is on the left side.  (Note: the Unicore primary antenna is the one connected on the right as seen from the top).

GPS_1_PROTOCOL.name: GPS_1_PROTOCOL
GPS_1_PROTOCOL.long_desc: Select the GPS protocol over serial.  Auto-detection will probe all protocols, and thus is a bit slower.

GPS_2_PROTOCOL.name: GPS_2_PROTOCOL
GPS_2_PROTOCOL.long_desc: Select the GPS protocol over serial.  Auto-detection will probe all protocols, and thus is a bit slower.

GPS_1_GNSS.name: GPS_1_GNSS
GPS_1_GNSS.short_desc: GNSS Systems for Primary GPS (integer bitmask)
GPS_1_GNSS.long_desc: This integer bitmask controls the set of GNSS systems used by the receiver. Check your receiver's documentation on how many systems are supported to be used in parallel.  Currently this functionality is just implemented for u-blox receivers.  When no bits are set, the receiver's default configuration should be used.  Set bits true to enable: 0 : Use GPS (with QZSS) 1 : Use SBAS (multiple GPS augmentation systems) 2 : Use Galileo 3 : Use BeiDou 4 : Use GLONASS 5 : Use NAVIC

Currently this functionality is just implemented for u-blox receivers.  When no bits are set, the receiver's default configuration should be used.  Set bits true to enable: 0 : Use GPS (with QZSS) 1 : Use SBAS (multiple GPS augmentation systems) 2 : Use Galileo 3 : Use BeiDou 4 : Use GLONASS 5 : Use NAVIC

UAVCAN_ECU_FUELT.name: UAVCAN_ECU_FUELT
UAVCAN_ECU_FUELT.long_desc: This parameter defines the type of fuel used in the vehicle's fuel tank.  0: Unknown 1: Liquid (e.g., gasoline, diesel) 2: Gas (e.g., hydrogen, methane, propane)

UAVCAN_LGT_ANTCL.name: UAVCAN_LGT_ANTCL
UAVCAN_LGT_ANTCL.long_desc: This parameter defines the minimum condition under which the system will command the ANTI_COLLISION lights on  0 - Always off 1 - When autopilot is armed 2 - When autopilot is prearmed 3 - Always on

UAVCAN_LGT_STROB.name: UAVCAN_LGT_STROB
UAVCAN_LGT_STROB.long_desc: This parameter defines the minimum condition under which the system will command the STROBE lights on  0 - Always off 1 - When autopilot is armed 2 - When autopilot is prearmed 3 - Always on

UAVCAN_LGT_NAV.name: UAVCAN_LGT_NAV
UAVCAN_LGT_NAV.long_desc: This parameter defines the minimum condition under which the system will command the RIGHT_OF_WAY lights on  0 - Always off 1 - When autopilot is armed 2 - When autopilot is prearmed 3 - Always on

UAVCAN_LGT_LAND.name: UAVCAN_LGT_LAND
UAVCAN_LGT_LAND.long_desc: This parameter defines the minimum condition under which the system will command the LIGHT_ID_LANDING lights on  0 - Always off 1 - When autopilot is armed 2 - When autopilot is prearmed 3 - Always on

UAVCAN_PUB_ARM.name: UAVCAN_PUB_ARM
UAVCAN_PUB_ARM.long_desc: Enable UAVCAN Arming Status stream publication uavcan::equipment::safety::ArmingStatus

UAVCAN_PUB_RTCM.name: UAVCAN_PUB_RTCM
UAVCAN_PUB_RTCM.long_desc: Enable UAVCAN RTCM stream publication uavcan::equipment::gnss::RTCMStream

UAVCAN_PUB_MBD.name: UAVCAN_PUB_MBD
UAVCAN_PUB_MBD.short_desc: publish moving baseline data RTCM stream
UAVCAN_PUB_MBD.long_desc: Enable UAVCAN RTCM stream publication ardupilot::gnss::MovingBaselineData

UAVCAN_SUB_BAT.name: UAVCAN_SUB_BAT
UAVCAN_SUB_BAT.long_desc: Enable UAVCAN battery subscription. uavcan::equipment::power::BatteryInfo ardupilot::equipment::power::BatteryInfoAux  0 - Disable 1 - Use raw data. Recommended for Smart battery 2 - Filter the data with internal battery library

UAVCAN_SUB_DPRES.name: UAVCAN_SUB_DPRES
UAVCAN_SUB_DPRES.long_desc: Enable UAVCAN differential pressure subscription. uavcan::equipment::air_data::RawAirData

UAVCAN_SUB_FUEL.name: UAVCAN_SUB_FUEL
UAVCAN_SUB_FUEL.long_desc: Enable UAVCAN fuel tank status subscription.

UAVCAN_SUB_GPS.name: UAVCAN_SUB_GPS
UAVCAN_SUB_GPS.long_desc: Enable UAVCAN GPS subscriptions. uavcan::equipment::gnss::Fix uavcan::equipment::gnss::Fix2 uavcan::equipment::gnss::Auxiliary

UAVCAN_SUB_GPS_R.name: UAVCAN_SUB_GPS_R
UAVCAN_SUB_GPS_R.long_desc: Enable UAVCAN GPS Relative subscription. ardupilot::gnss::RelPosHeading

UAVCAN_SUB_ICE.name: UAVCAN_SUB_ICE
UAVCAN_SUB_ICE.long_desc: Enable UAVCAN internal combustion engine (ICE) subscription. uavcan::equipment::ice::reciprocating::Status

VOXL2_IO_BAUD.name: VOXL2_IO_BAUD
VOXL2_IO_BAUD.long_desc: Default rate is 921600, which is used for communicating with VOXL2_IO board

VOXL2_IO_DIS.name: VOXL2_IO_DIS
VOXL2_IO_DIS.long_desc: Pulse duration in disabled state (microseconds) for VOXL2_IO board

ADSB_SQUAWK.name: ADSB_SQUAWK
ADSB_SQUAWK.long_desc: This parameter defines the squawk code. Value should be between 0000 and 7777.

ADSB_LIST_MAX.name: ADSB_LIST_MAX
ADSB_LIST_MAX.long_desc: Change number of targets to track

ADSB_ICAO_ID.name: ADSB_ICAO_ID
ADSB_ICAO_ID.long_desc: Defines the ICAO ID of the vehicle

ADSB_LEN_WIDTH.name: ADSB_LEN_WIDTH
ADSB_LEN_WIDTH.long_desc: Report the length and width of the vehicle in meters. In most cases, use '1' for the smallest vehicle size.

ADSB_EMIT_TYPE.name: ADSB_EMIT_TYPE
ADSB_EMIT_TYPE.long_desc: Configure the emitter type of the vehicle.

ADSB_MAX_SPEED.name: ADSB_MAX_SPEED
ADSB_MAX_SPEED.long_desc: Informs ADSB vehicles of this vehicle's max speed capability

ADSB_ICAO_SPECL.name: ADSB_ICAO_SPECL
ADSB_ICAO_SPECL.long_desc: This vehicle is always tracked. Use 0 to disable.

ADSB_CALLSIGN_1.name: ADSB_CALLSIGN_1
ADSB_CALLSIGN_1.long_desc: Sets first 4 characters of a total of 8. Valid characters are A-Z, 0-9, " ". Example "PX4 " -> 1347957792 For CALLSIGN shorter than 8 characters use the null terminator at the end '\0'.

ADSB_CALLSIGN_2.name: ADSB_CALLSIGN_2
ADSB_CALLSIGN_2.long_desc: Sets second 4 characters of a total of 8. Valid characters are A-Z, 0-9, " " only. Example "TEST" -> 1413829460 For CALLSIGN shorter than 8 characters use the null terminator at the end '\0'.

CBRK_SUPPLY_CHK.name: CBRK_SUPPLY_CHK
CBRK_SUPPLY_CHK.short_desc: Circuit breaker for power supply check
CBRK_SUPPLY_CHK.long_desc: Setting this parameter to 894281 will disable the power valid checks in the commander. WARNING: ENABLING THIS CIRCUIT BREAKER IS AT OWN RISK

CBRK_IO_SAFETY.name: CBRK_IO_SAFETY
CBRK_IO_SAFETY.long_desc: Setting this parameter to 22027 will disable IO safety. WARNING: ENABLING THIS CIRCUIT BREAKER IS AT OWN RISK

CBRK_FLIGHTTERM.name: CBRK_FLIGHTTERM
CBRK_FLIGHTTERM.long_desc: Setting this parameter to 121212 will disable the flight termination action if triggered by the FailureDetector logic or if FMU is lost. This circuit breaker does not affect the RC loss, data link loss, geofence, and takeoff failure detection safety logic.

CBRK_BUZZER.name: CBRK_BUZZER
CBRK_BUZZER.long_desc: Setting this parameter to 782097 will disable the buzzer audio notification.  Setting this parameter to 782090 will disable the startup tune, while keeping all others enabled.

CBRK_USB_CHK.name: CBRK_USB_CHK
CBRK_USB_CHK.short_desc: Circuit breaker for USB link check
CBRK_USB_CHK.long_desc: Setting this parameter to 197848 will disable the USB connected checks in the commander, setting it to 0 keeps them enabled (recommended).  We are generally recommending to not fly with the USB link connected and production vehicles should set this parameter to zero to prevent users from flying USB powered. However, for R&D purposes it has proven over the years to work just fine.

CBRK_VTOLARMING.name: CBRK_VTOLARMING
CBRK_VTOLARMING.short_desc: Circuit breaker for arming in fixed-wing mode check
CBRK_VTOLARMING.long_desc: Setting this parameter to 159753 will enable arming in fixed-wing mode for VTOLs. WARNING: ENABLING THIS CIRCUIT BREAKER IS AT OWN RISK

CP_DIST.name: CP_DIST
CP_DIST.short_desc: Minimum distance the vehicle should keep to all obstacles
CP_DIST.long_desc: Only used in Position mode. Collision avoidance is disabled by setting this parameter to a negative value

CP_DELAY.name: CP_DELAY
CP_DELAY.short_desc: Average delay of the range sensor message plus the tracking delay of the position controller in seconds

CP_GUIDE_ANG.name: CP_GUIDE_ANG
CP_GUIDE_ANG.short_desc: Angle left/right from the commanded setpoint by which the collision prevention algorithm can choose to change the setpoint direction

CP_GO_NO_DATA.name: CP_GO_NO_DATA
CP_GO_NO_DATA.short_desc: Boolean to allow moving into directions where there is no sensor data (outside FOV)

FW_THR_TRIM.name: FW_THR_TRIM
FW_THR_TRIM.long_desc: Required throttle (at sea level, standard atmosphere) for level flight at FW_AIRSPD_TRIM

FW_THR_ASPD_MIN.name: FW_THR_ASPD_MIN
FW_THR_ASPD_MIN.long_desc: Required throttle (at sea level, standard atmosphere) for level flight at minimum airspeed FW_AIRSPD_MIN  Set to 0 to disable mapping of airspeed to trim throttle below FW_AIRSPD_TRIM.

FW_THR_ASPD_MAX.name: FW_THR_ASPD_MAX
FW_THR_ASPD_MAX.long_desc: Required throttle (at sea level, standard atmosphere) for level flight at maximum airspeed FW_AIRSPD_MAX  Set to 0 to disable mapping of airspeed to trim throttle.

FW_SERVICE_CEIL.name: FW_SERVICE_CEIL
FW_SERVICE_CEIL.long_desc: Altitude in standard atmosphere at which the vehicle in normal configuration (WEIGHT_BASE) is still able to achieve a maximum climb rate of 0.5m/s at maximum throttle (FW_THR_MAX). Used to compensate for air density in FW_T_CLMB_MAX. Set negative to disable.

WEIGHT_BASE.name: WEIGHT_BASE
WEIGHT_BASE.long_desc: This is the weight of the vehicle at which it's performance limits were derived. A zero or negative value disables trim throttle and minimum airspeed compensation based on weight.

WEIGHT_GROSS.name: WEIGHT_GROSS
WEIGHT_GROSS.long_desc: This is the actual weight of the vehicle at any time. This value will differ from WEIGHT_BASE in case weight was added or removed from the base weight. Examples are the addition of payloads or larger batteries. A zero or negative value disables trim throttle and minimum airspeed compensation based on weight.

FW_T_CLMB_MAX.name: FW_T_CLMB_MAX
FW_T_CLMB_MAX.long_desc: This is the maximum calibrated climb rate that the aircraft can achieve with the throttle set to FW_THR_MAX and the airspeed set to the trim value. For electric aircraft make sure this number can be achieved towards the end of flight when the battery voltage has reduced.

FW_T_SINK_MIN.name: FW_T_SINK_MIN
FW_T_SINK_MIN.long_desc: This is the minimum calibrated sink rate of the aircraft with the throttle set to THR_MIN and flown at the same airspeed as used to measure FW_T_CLMB_MAX.

FW_AIRSPD_TRIM.name: FW_AIRSPD_TRIM
FW_AIRSPD_TRIM.long_desc: The trim CAS (calibrated airspeed) of the vehicle. If an airspeed controller is active, this is the default airspeed setpoint that the controller will try to achieve. This value corresponds to the trim airspeed with the default load factor (level flight, default weight).

FW_AIRSPD_STALL.name: FW_AIRSPD_STALL
FW_AIRSPD_STALL.long_desc: The stall airspeed (calibrated airspeed) of the vehicle. It is used for airspeed sensor failure detection and for the control surface scaling airspeed limits.

FW_AIRSPD_MIN.name: FW_AIRSPD_MIN
FW_AIRSPD_MIN.long_desc: The minimal airspeed (calibrated airspeed) the user is able to command. Further, if the airspeed falls below this value, the TECS controller will try to increase airspeed more aggressively. Has to be set according to the vehicle's stall speed (which should be set in FW_AIRSPD_STALL), with some margin between the stall speed and minimum airspeed. This value corresponds to the desired minimum speed with the default load factor (level flight, default weight), and is automatically adpated to the current load factor (calculated from roll setpoint and WEIGHT_GROSS/WEIGHT_BASE).

FW_AIRSPD_MAX.name: FW_AIRSPD_MAX
FW_AIRSPD_MAX.long_desc: The maximal airspeed (calibrated airspeed) the user is able to command.

SYS_RGB_MAXBRT.name: SYS_RGB_MAXBRT
SYS_RGB_MAXBRT.long_desc: Set to 0 to disable, 1 for maximum brightness

THR_MDL_FAC.name: THR_MDL_FAC
THR_MDL_FAC.short_desc: Thrust to motor control signal model parameter
THR_MDL_FAC.long_desc: Parameter used to model the nonlinear relationship between motor control signal (e.g. PWM) and static thrust.  The model is: rel_thrust = factor * rel_signal^2 + (1-factor) * rel_signal, where rel_thrust is the normalized thrust between 0 and 1, and rel_signal is the relative motor control signal between 0 and 1.

MC_AIRMODE.name: MC_AIRMODE
MC_AIRMODE.long_desc: The air-mode enables the mixer to increase the total thrust of the multirotor in order to keep attitude and rate control even at low and high throttle.  This function should be disabled during tuning as it will help the controller to diverge if the closed-loop is unstable (i.e. the vehicle is not tuned yet).  Enabling air-mode for yaw requires the use of an arming switch.

SYS_AUTOSTART.name: SYS_AUTOSTART
SYS_AUTOSTART.long_desc: CHANGING THIS VALUE REQUIRES A RESTART. Defines the auto-start script used to bootstrap the system.

SYS_AUTOCONFIG.name: SYS_AUTOCONFIG
SYS_AUTOCONFIG.long_desc: Set to 1 to reset parameters on next system startup (setting defaults). Platform-specific values are used if available. RC* parameters are preserved.

SYS_HITL.name: SYS_HITL
SYS_HITL.short_desc: Enable HITL/SIH mode on next boot
SYS_HITL.long_desc: While enabled the system will boot in Hardware-In-The-Loop (HITL) or Simulation-In-Hardware (SIH) mode and not enable all sensors and checks. When disabled the same vehicle can be flown normally.  Set to 'external HITL', if the system should perform as if it were a real vehicle (the only difference to a real system is then only the parameter value, which can be used for log analysis).

SYS_PARAM_VER.name: SYS_PARAM_VER
SYS_PARAM_VER.long_desc: This is used internally only: an airframe configuration might set an expected parameter version value via PARAM_DEFAULTS_VER. This is checked on bootup against SYS_PARAM_VER, and if they do not match, parameters are reset and reloaded from the airframe configuration.

SYS_CAL_GYRO.name: SYS_CAL_GYRO
SYS_CAL_GYRO.short_desc: Enable auto start of rate gyro thermal calibration at the next power up.
SYS_CAL_GYRO.long_desc: 0 : Set to 0 to do nothing 1 : Set to 1 to start a calibration at next boot This parameter is reset to zero when the temperature calibration starts.  default (0, no calibration)

SYS_CAL_ACCEL.name: SYS_CAL_ACCEL
SYS_CAL_ACCEL.short_desc: Enable auto start of accelerometer thermal calibration at the next power up.
SYS_CAL_ACCEL.long_desc: 0 : Set to 0 to do nothing 1 : Set to 1 to start a calibration at next boot This parameter is reset to zero when the temperature calibration starts.  default (0, no calibration)

SYS_CAL_BARO.name: SYS_CAL_BARO
SYS_CAL_BARO.short_desc: Enable auto start of barometer thermal calibration at the next power up.
SYS_CAL_BARO.long_desc: 0 : Set to 0 to do nothing 1 : Set to 1 to start a calibration at next boot This parameter is reset to zero when the temperature calibration starts.  default (0, no calibration)

SYS_CAL_TDEL.name: SYS_CAL_TDEL
SYS_CAL_TDEL.short_desc: Required temperature rise during thermal calibration
SYS_CAL_TDEL.long_desc: A temperature increase greater than this value is required during calibration. Calibration will complete for each sensor when the temperature increase above the starting temperature exceeds the value set by SYS_CAL_TDEL. If the temperature rise is insufficient, the calibration will continue indefinitely and the board will need to be repowered to exit.

SYS_CAL_TMIN.name: SYS_CAL_TMIN
SYS_CAL_TMIN.short_desc: Minimum starting temperature for thermal calibration
SYS_CAL_TMIN.long_desc: Temperature calibration for each sensor will ignore data if the temperature is lower than the value set by SYS_CAL_TMIN.

SYS_CAL_TMAX.name: SYS_CAL_TMAX
SYS_CAL_TMAX.short_desc: Maximum starting temperature for thermal calibration
SYS_CAL_TMAX.long_desc: Temperature calibration will not start if the temperature of any sensor is higher than the value set by SYS_CAL_TMAX.

SYS_HAS_GPS.name: SYS_HAS_GPS
SYS_HAS_GPS.short_desc: Control if the vehicle has a GPS
SYS_HAS_GPS.long_desc: Disable this if the system has no GPS. If disabled, the sensors hub will not process sensor_gps, and GPS will not be available for the rest of the system.

SYS_HAS_MAG.name: SYS_HAS_MAG
SYS_HAS_MAG.short_desc: Control if and how many magnetometers are expected
SYS_HAS_MAG.long_desc: 0: System has no magnetometer, preflight checks should pass without one. 1-N: Require the presence of N magnetometer sensors for check to pass.

SYS_HAS_BARO.name: SYS_HAS_BARO
SYS_HAS_BARO.short_desc: Control if the vehicle has a barometer
SYS_HAS_BARO.long_desc: Disable this if the board has no barometer, such as some of the Omnibus F4 SD variants. If disabled, the preflight checks will not check for the presence of a barometer.

SYS_HAS_NUM_ASPD.name: SYS_HAS_NUM_ASPD
SYS_HAS_NUM_ASPD.short_desc: Control if the vehicle has an airspeed sensor
SYS_HAS_NUM_ASPD.long_desc: Set this to 0 if the board has no airspeed sensor. If set to 0, the preflight checks will not check for the presence of an airspeed sensor.

SYS_HAS_NUM_DIST.name: SYS_HAS_NUM_DIST
SYS_HAS_NUM_DIST.short_desc: Number of distance sensors to check being available
SYS_HAS_NUM_DIST.long_desc: The preflight check will fail if fewer than this number of distance sensors with valid data is present.  Disable the check with 0.

SYS_FAC_CAL_MODE.name: SYS_FAC_CAL_MODE
SYS_FAC_CAL_MODE.long_desc: If enabled, future sensor calibrations will be stored to /fs/mtd_caldata.  Note: this is only supported on boards with a separate calibration storage fs/mtd_caldata.

SYS_BL_UPDATE.name: SYS_BL_UPDATE
SYS_BL_UPDATE.long_desc: If enabled, update the bootloader on the next boot.  WARNING: do not cut the power during an update process, otherwise you will have to recover using some alternative method (e.g. JTAG).  Instructions: - Insert an SD card - Enable this parameter - Reboot the board (plug the power or send a reboot command) - Wait until the board comes back up (or at least 2 minutes) - If it does not come back, check the file bootlog.txt on the SD card

SYS_FAILURE_EN.name: SYS_FAILURE_EN
SYS_FAILURE_EN.long_desc: If enabled allows MAVLink INJECT_FAILURE commands.  WARNING: the failures can easily cause crashes and are to be used with caution!

WV_GAIN.name: WV_GAIN
WV_GAIN.long_desc: The desired gain to convert roll sp into yaw rate sp.

WV_ROLL_MIN.name: WV_ROLL_MIN
WV_ROLL_MIN.short_desc: Minimum roll angle setpoint for weathervane controller to demand a yaw-rate.

WV_YRATE_MAX.name: WV_YRATE_MAX
WV_YRATE_MAX.short_desc: Maximum yawrate the weathervane controller is allowed to demand.

ASPD_WIND_NSD.name: ASPD_WIND_NSD
ASPD_WIND_NSD.short_desc: Wind estimator wind process noise spectral density
ASPD_WIND_NSD.long_desc: Wind process noise of the internal wind estimator(s) of the airspeed selector. When unaided, the wind estimate uncertainty (1-sigma, in m/s) increases by this amount every second.

ASPD_SCALE_NSD.name: ASPD_SCALE_NSD
ASPD_SCALE_NSD.short_desc: Wind estimator true airspeed scale process noise spectral density
ASPD_SCALE_NSD.long_desc: Airspeed scale process noise of the internal wind estimator(s) of the airspeed selector. When unaided, the scale uncertainty (1-sigma, unitless) increases by this amount every second.

ASPD_TAS_NOISE.name: ASPD_TAS_NOISE
ASPD_TAS_NOISE.short_desc: Wind estimator true airspeed measurement noise
ASPD_TAS_NOISE.long_desc: True airspeed measurement noise of the internal wind estimator(s) of the airspeed selector.

ASPD_BETA_NOISE.name: ASPD_BETA_NOISE
ASPD_BETA_NOISE.long_desc: Sideslip measurement noise of the internal wind estimator(s) of the airspeed selector.

ASPD_TAS_GATE.name: ASPD_TAS_GATE
ASPD_TAS_GATE.short_desc: Gate size for true airspeed fusion
ASPD_TAS_GATE.long_desc: Sets the number of standard deviations used by the innovation consistency test.

ASPD_BETA_GATE.name: ASPD_BETA_GATE
ASPD_BETA_GATE.short_desc: Gate size for sideslip angle fusion
ASPD_BETA_GATE.long_desc: Sets the number of standard deviations used by the innovation consistency test.

ASPD_SCALE_APPLY.name: ASPD_SCALE_APPLY
ASPD_SCALE_APPLY.short_desc: Controls when to apply the new estimated airspeed scale(s)

ASPD_SCALE_1.name: ASPD_SCALE_1
ASPD_SCALE_1.long_desc: This is the scale IAS --> CAS of the first airspeed sensor instance

ASPD_SCALE_2.name: ASPD_SCALE_2
ASPD_SCALE_2.long_desc: This is the scale IAS --> CAS of the second airspeed sensor instance

ASPD_SCALE_3.name: ASPD_SCALE_3
ASPD_SCALE_3.long_desc: This is the scale IAS --> CAS of the third airspeed sensor instance

ASPD_PRIMARY.name: ASPD_PRIMARY
ASPD_PRIMARY.short_desc: Index or primary airspeed measurement source

ASPD_DO_CHECKS.name: ASPD_DO_CHECKS
ASPD_DO_CHECKS.long_desc: Controls which checks are run to check airspeed data for validity. Only applied if ASPD_PRIMARY > 0.

ASPD_FALLBACK_GW.name: ASPD_FALLBACK_GW
ASPD_FALLBACK_GW.short_desc: Enable fallback to sensor-less airspeed estimation
ASPD_FALLBACK_GW.long_desc: If set to true and airspeed checks are enabled, it will use a sensor-less airspeed estimation based on groundspeed minus windspeed if no other airspeed sensor available to fall back to.

ASPD_FS_INNOV.name: ASPD_FS_INNOV
ASPD_FS_INNOV.long_desc: This specifies the minimum airspeed innovation required to trigger a failsafe. Larger values make the check less sensitive, smaller values make it more sensitive. Large innovations indicate an inconsistency between predicted (groundspeed - windspeeed) and measured airspeed. The time required to detect a fault when the threshold is exceeded depends on the size of the exceedance and is controlled by the ASPD_FS_INTEG parameter.

ASPD_FS_INTEG.name: ASPD_FS_INTEG
ASPD_FS_INTEG.long_desc: This sets the time integral of airspeed innovation exceedance above ASPD_FS_INNOV required to trigger a failsafe. Larger values make the check less sensitive, smaller positive values make it more sensitive.

ASPD_FS_T_STOP.name: ASPD_FS_T_STOP
ASPD_FS_T_STOP.long_desc: Delay before stopping use of airspeed sensor if checks indicate sensor is bad.

ASPD_FS_T_START.name: ASPD_FS_T_START
ASPD_FS_T_START.long_desc: Delay before switching back to using airspeed sensor if checks indicate sensor is good. Set to a negative value to disable the re-enabling in flight.

ASPD_WERR_THR.name: ASPD_WERR_THR
ASPD_WERR_THR.short_desc: Horizontal wind uncertainty threshold for synthetic airspeed.
ASPD_WERR_THR.long_desc: The synthetic airspeed estimate (from groundspeed and heading) will be declared valid as soon and as long the horizontal wind uncertainty is below this value.

ASPD_FP_T_WINDOW.name: ASPD_FP_T_WINDOW
ASPD_FP_T_WINDOW.short_desc: First principle airspeed check time window
ASPD_FP_T_WINDOW.long_desc: Window for comparing airspeed change to throttle and pitch change. Triggers when the airspeed change within this window is negative while throttle increases and the vehicle pitches down. Is meant to catch degrading airspeed blockages as can happen when flying through icing conditions. Relies on  FW_THR_TRIM being set accurately.

ATT_EN.name: ATT_EN
ATT_EN.long_desc: Enable standalone quaternion based attitude estimator.

ATT_W_MAG.name: ATT_W_MAG
ATT_W_MAG.long_desc: Set to 0 to avoid using the magnetometer.

ATT_MAG_DECL.name: ATT_MAG_DECL
ATT_MAG_DECL.long_desc: This parameter is not used in normal operation, as the declination is looked up based on the GPS coordinates of the vehicle.

ATT_EXT_HDG_M.name: ATT_EXT_HDG_M
ATT_EXT_HDG_M.short_desc: External heading usage mode (from Motion capture/Vision)
ATT_EXT_HDG_M.long_desc: Set to 1 to use heading estimate from vision. Set to 2 to use heading from motion capture.

ATT_ACC_COMP.name: ATT_ACC_COMP
ATT_ACC_COMP.short_desc: Acceleration compensation based on GPS velocity.

BAT_V_OFFS_CURR.name: BAT_V_OFFS_CURR
BAT_V_OFFS_CURR.short_desc: Offset in volt as seen by the ADC input of the current sensor.
BAT_V_OFFS_CURR.long_desc: This offset will be subtracted before calculating the battery current based on the voltage.

BAT_ADC_CHANNEL.name: BAT_ADC_CHANNEL
BAT_ADC_CHANNEL.short_desc: This parameter is deprecated. Please use BAT1_I_CHANNEL.

TRIM_ROLL.name: TRIM_ROLL
TRIM_ROLL.long_desc: The trim value is the actuator control value the system needs for straight and level flight.

TRIM_PITCH.name: TRIM_PITCH
TRIM_PITCH.long_desc: The trim value is the actuator control value the system needs for straight and level flight.

TRIM_YAW.name: TRIM_YAW
TRIM_YAW.long_desc: The trim value is the actuator control value the system needs for straight and level flight.

COM_DL_LOSS_T.name: COM_DL_LOSS_T
COM_DL_LOSS_T.long_desc: After this amount of seconds without datalink, the GCS connection lost mode triggers

COM_HLDL_LOSS_T.name: COM_HLDL_LOSS_T
COM_HLDL_LOSS_T.short_desc: High Latency Datalink loss time threshold
COM_HLDL_LOSS_T.long_desc: After this amount of seconds without datalink the data link lost mode triggers

COM_HLDL_REG_T.name: COM_HLDL_REG_T
COM_HLDL_REG_T.short_desc: High Latency Datalink regain time threshold
COM_HLDL_REG_T.long_desc: After a data link loss: after this number of seconds with a healthy datalink the 'datalink loss' flag is set back to false

COM_RC_LOSS_T.name: COM_RC_LOSS_T
COM_RC_LOSS_T.long_desc: The time in seconds without a new setpoint from RC or Joystick, after which the connection is considered lost. This must be kept short as the vehicle will use the last supplied setpoint until the timeout triggers.

COM_HOME_EN.name: COM_HOME_EN
COM_HOME_EN.long_desc: Set home position automatically if possible.

COM_HOME_IN_AIR.name: COM_HOME_IN_AIR
COM_HOME_IN_AIR.short_desc: Allows setting the home position after takeoff
COM_HOME_IN_AIR.long_desc: If set to true, the autopilot is allowed to set its home position after takeoff The true home position is back-computed if a local position is estimate if available. If no local position is available, home is set to the current position.

COM_RC_IN_MODE.name: COM_RC_IN_MODE
COM_RC_IN_MODE.long_desc: A value of 0 enables RC transmitter control (only). A valid RC transmitter calibration is required. A value of 1 allows joystick control only. RC input handling and the associated checks are disabled. A value of 2 allows either RC Transmitter or Joystick input. The first valid input is used, will fallback to other sources if the input stream becomes invalid. A value of 3 allows either input from RC or joystick. The first available source is selected and used until reboot. A value of 4 ignores any stick input.

COM_RC_ARM_HYST.name: COM_RC_ARM_HYST
COM_RC_ARM_HYST.long_desc: The default value of 1000 requires the stick to be held in the arm or disarm position for 1 second.

COM_DISARM_LAND.name: COM_DISARM_LAND
COM_DISARM_LAND.short_desc: Time-out for auto disarm after landing
COM_DISARM_LAND.long_desc: A non-zero, positive value specifies the time-out period in seconds after which the vehicle will be automatically disarmed in case a landing situation has been detected during this period.  A zero or negative value means that automatic disarming triggered by landing detection is disabled.

COM_DISARM_PRFLT.name: COM_DISARM_PRFLT
COM_DISARM_PRFLT.short_desc: Time-out for auto disarm if not taking off
COM_DISARM_PRFLT.long_desc: A non-zero, positive value specifies the time in seconds, within which the vehicle is expected to take off after arming. In case the vehicle didn't takeoff within the timeout it disarms again.  A negative value disables autmoatic disarming triggered by a pre-takeoff timeout.

COM_ARM_WO_GPS.name: COM_ARM_WO_GPS
COM_ARM_WO_GPS.long_desc: Measures taken when a check defined by EKF2_GPS_CHECK is failing.

COM_ARM_SWISBTN.name: COM_ARM_SWISBTN
COM_ARM_SWISBTN.short_desc: Arm switch is a momentary button
COM_ARM_SWISBTN.long_desc: 0: Arming/disarming triggers on switch transition. 1: Arming/disarming triggers when holding the momentary button down for COM_RC_ARM_HYST like the stick gesture.

COM_DISARM_MAN.name: COM_DISARM_MAN
COM_DISARM_MAN.short_desc: Allow disarming via switch/stick/button on multicopters in manual thrust modes
COM_DISARM_MAN.long_desc: 0: Disallow disarming when not landed 1: Allow disarming in multicopter flight in modes where the thrust is directly controlled by thr throttle stick e.g. Stabilized, Acro

COM_LOW_BAT_ACT.name: COM_LOW_BAT_ACT
COM_LOW_BAT_ACT.long_desc: Action the system takes at critical battery. See also BAT_CRIT_THR and BAT_EMERGEN_THR for definition of battery states.

COM_FAIL_ACT_T.name: COM_FAIL_ACT_T
COM_FAIL_ACT_T.short_desc: Delay between failsafe condition triggered and failsafe reaction
COM_FAIL_ACT_T.long_desc: Before entering failsafe (RTL, Land, Hold), wait COM_FAIL_ACT_T seconds in Hold mode for the user to realize. During that time the user cannot take over control via the stick override feature (see COM_RC_OVERRIDE). Afterwards the configured failsafe action is triggered and the user may use stick override.  A zero value disables the delay and the user cannot take over via stick movements (switching modes is still allowed).

COM_IMB_PROP_ACT.name: COM_IMB_PROP_ACT
COM_IMB_PROP_ACT.long_desc: Action the system takes when an imbalanced propeller is detected by the failure detector. See also FD_IMB_PROP_THR to set the failure threshold.

COM_OF_LOSS_T.name: COM_OF_LOSS_T
COM_OF_LOSS_T.short_desc: Time-out to wait when offboard connection is lost before triggering offboard lost action.

COM_OBL_RC_ACT.name: COM_OBL_RC_ACT
COM_OBL_RC_ACT.long_desc: The offboard loss failsafe will only be entered after a timeout, set by COM_OF_LOSS_T in seconds.

COM_OBC_LOSS_T.name: COM_OBC_LOSS_T
COM_OBC_LOSS_T.short_desc: Time-out to wait when onboard computer connection is lost before warning about loss connection.

COM_ARM_IMU_ACC.name: COM_ARM_IMU_ACC
COM_ARM_IMU_ACC.short_desc: Maximum accelerometer inconsistency between IMU units that will allow arming

COM_ARM_IMU_GYR.name: COM_ARM_IMU_GYR
COM_ARM_IMU_GYR.short_desc: Maximum rate gyro inconsistency between IMU units that will allow arming

COM_ARM_MAG_ANG.name: COM_ARM_MAG_ANG
COM_ARM_MAG_ANG.short_desc: Maximum magnetic field inconsistency between units that will allow arming

COM_ARM_MAG_STR.name: COM_ARM_MAG_STR
COM_ARM_MAG_STR.long_desc: Check if the estimator detects a strong magnetic disturbance (check enabled by EKF2_MAG_CHECK)

COM_RC_OVERRIDE.name: COM_RC_OVERRIDE
COM_RC_OVERRIDE.short_desc: Enable RC stick override of auto and/or offboard modes
COM_RC_OVERRIDE.long_desc: When RC stick override is enabled, moving the RC sticks more than COM_RC_STICK_OV immediately gives control back to the pilot by switching to Position mode and if position is unavailable Altitude mode. Note: Only has an effect on multicopters, and VTOLs in multicopter mode.

COM_RC_STICK_OV.name: COM_RC_STICK_OV
COM_RC_STICK_OV.long_desc: If COM_RC_OVERRIDE is enabled and the joystick input is moved more than this threshold the autopilot the pilot takes over control.

COM_ARM_MIS_REQ.name: COM_ARM_MIS_REQ
COM_ARM_MIS_REQ.long_desc: The default allows to arm the vehicle without a valid mission.

COM_POSCTL_NAVL.name: COM_POSCTL_NAVL
COM_POSCTL_NAVL.long_desc: This sets the flight mode that will be used if navigation accuracy is no longer adequate for position control in manual Position mode.

COM_ARM_AUTH_REQ.name: COM_ARM_AUTH_REQ
COM_ARM_AUTH_REQ.long_desc: By default off. The default allows to arm the vehicle without a arm authorization.

COM_ARM_AUTH_ID.name: COM_ARM_AUTH_ID
COM_ARM_AUTH_ID.long_desc: Used if arm authorization is requested by COM_ARM_AUTH_REQ.

COM_ARM_AUTH_MET.name: COM_ARM_AUTH_MET
COM_ARM_AUTH_MET.long_desc: Methods: - one arm: request authorization and arm when authorization is received - two step arm: 1st arm command request an authorization and 2nd arm command arm the drone if authorized  Used if arm authorization is requested by COM_ARM_AUTH_REQ.

COM_ARM_AUTH_TO.name: COM_ARM_AUTH_TO
COM_ARM_AUTH_TO.long_desc: Timeout for authorizer answer. Used if arm authorization is requested by COM_ARM_AUTH_REQ.

COM_POS_FS_EPH.name: COM_POS_FS_EPH
COM_POS_FS_EPH.long_desc: This is the horizontal position error (EPH) threshold that will trigger a failsafe. The default is appropriate for a multicopter. Can be increased for a fixed-wing. If the previous position error was below this threshold, there is an additional factor of 2.5 applied (threshold for invalidation 2.5 times the one for validation).  Set to -1 to disable.

COM_VEL_FS_EVH.name: COM_VEL_FS_EVH
COM_VEL_FS_EVH.long_desc: This is the horizontal velocity error (EVH) threshold that will trigger a failsafe. The default is appropriate for a multicopter. Can be increased for a fixed-wing. If the previous velocity error was below this threshold, there is an additional factor of 2.5 applied (threshold for invalidation 2.5 times the one for validation).

COM_FLIGHT_UUID.name: COM_FLIGHT_UUID
COM_FLIGHT_UUID.long_desc: This number is incremented automatically after every flight on disarming in order to remember the next flight UUID. The first flight is 0.

COM_TAKEOFF_ACT.name: COM_TAKEOFF_ACT
COM_TAKEOFF_ACT.short_desc: Action after TAKEOFF has been accepted.
COM_TAKEOFF_ACT.long_desc: The mode transition after TAKEOFF has completed successfully.

NAV_DLL_ACT.name: NAV_DLL_ACT
NAV_DLL_ACT.short_desc: Set GCS connection loss failsafe mode
NAV_DLL_ACT.long_desc: The GCS connection loss failsafe will only be entered after a timeout, set by COM_DL_LOSS_T in seconds. Once the timeout occurs the selected action will be executed.

NAV_RCL_ACT.name: NAV_RCL_ACT
NAV_RCL_ACT.long_desc: The RC loss failsafe will only be entered after a timeout, set by COM_RC_LOSS_T in seconds. If RC input checks have been disabled by setting the COM_RC_IN_MODE param it will not be triggered.

COM_RCL_EXCEPT.name: COM_RCL_EXCEPT
COM_RCL_EXCEPT.long_desc: Specify modes in which RC loss is ignored and the failsafe action not triggered.

COM_ACT_FAIL_ACT.name: COM_ACT_FAIL_ACT
COM_ACT_FAIL_ACT.short_desc: Set the actuator failure failsafe mode
COM_ACT_FAIL_ACT.long_desc: Note: actuator failure needs to be enabled and configured via FD_ACT_ parameters.

COM_PARACHUTE.name: COM_PARACHUTE
COM_PARACHUTE.short_desc: Expect and require a healthy MAVLink parachute system

COM_FLT_PROFILE.name: COM_FLT_PROFILE
COM_FLT_PROFILE.long_desc: Describes the intended use of the vehicle. Can be used by ground control software or log post processing. This param does not influence the behavior within the firmware. This means for example the control logic is independent of the setting of this param (but depends on other params).

COM_ARM_CHK_ESCS.name: COM_ARM_CHK_ESCS
COM_ARM_CHK_ESCS.short_desc: Enable checks on ESCs that report telemetry.
COM_ARM_CHK_ESCS.long_desc: If this parameter is set, the system will check ESC's online status and failures. This param is specific for ESCs reporting status. It shall be used only if ESCs support telemetry.

COM_PREARM_MODE.name: COM_PREARM_MODE
COM_PREARM_MODE.long_desc: Condition to enter the prearmed state, an intermediate state between disarmed and armed in which non-throttling actuators are active.

COM_FORCE_SAFETY.name: COM_FORCE_SAFETY
COM_FORCE_SAFETY.long_desc: Force safety when the vehicle disarms

COM_MOT_TEST_EN.name: COM_MOT_TEST_EN
COM_MOT_TEST_EN.long_desc: If set, enables the actuator test interface via MAVLink (ACTUATOR_TEST), that allows spinning the motors and moving the servos for testing purposes.

COM_KILL_DISARM.name: COM_KILL_DISARM
COM_KILL_DISARM.short_desc: Timeout value for disarming when kill switch is engaged

COM_CPU_MAX.name: COM_CPU_MAX
COM_CPU_MAX.short_desc: Maximum allowed CPU load to still arm.
COM_CPU_MAX.long_desc: The check fails if the CPU load is above this threshold for 2s.  A negative value disables the check.

COM_RAM_MAX.name: COM_RAM_MAX
COM_RAM_MAX.short_desc: Maximum allowed RAM usage to pass checks
COM_RAM_MAX.long_desc: The check fails if the RAM usage is above this threshold.  A negative value disables the check.

COM_POWER_COUNT.name: COM_POWER_COUNT
COM_POWER_COUNT.short_desc: Required number of redundant power modules
COM_POWER_COUNT.long_desc: This configures a check to verify the expected number of 5V rail power supplies are present. By default only one is expected. Note: CBRK_SUPPLY_CHK disables all power checks including this one.

COM_LKDOWN_TKO.name: COM_LKDOWN_TKO
COM_LKDOWN_TKO.short_desc: Timeout for detecting a failure after takeoff
COM_LKDOWN_TKO.long_desc: A non-zero, positive value specifies the timeframe in seconds within failure detector is allowed to disarm the vehicle if attitude exceeds the limits defined in FD_FAIL_P and FD_FAIL_R. The check is not executed for flight modes that do support acrobatic maneuvers, e.g: Acro (MC/FW) and Manual (FW). A zero or negative value means that the check is disabled.

COM_ARM_SDCARD.name: COM_ARM_SDCARD
COM_ARM_SDCARD.short_desc: Enable FMU SD card detection check
COM_ARM_SDCARD.long_desc: This check detects if the FMU SD card is missing. Depending on the value of the parameter, the check can be disabled, warn only or deny arming.

COM_ARM_HFLT_CHK.name: COM_ARM_HFLT_CHK
COM_ARM_HFLT_CHK.short_desc: Enable FMU SD card hardfault detection check
COM_ARM_HFLT_CHK.long_desc: This check detects if there are hardfault files present on the SD card. If so, and the parameter is enabled, arming is prevented.

COM_ARM_ODID.name: COM_ARM_ODID
COM_ARM_ODID.short_desc: Enable Drone ID system detection and health check
COM_ARM_ODID.long_desc: This check detects if the Open Drone ID system is missing. Depending on the value of the parameter, the check can be disabled, warn only or deny arming.

COM_SPOOLUP_TIME.name: COM_SPOOLUP_TIME
COM_SPOOLUP_TIME.short_desc: Enforced delay between arming and further navigation
COM_SPOOLUP_TIME.long_desc: The minimal time from arming the motors until moving the vehicle is possible is COM_SPOOLUP_TIME seconds. Goal: - Motors and propellers spool up to idle speed before getting commanded to spin faster - Timeout for ESCs and smart batteries to successfulyy do failure checks e.g. for stuck rotors before the vehicle is off the ground

COM_WIND_WARN.name: COM_WIND_WARN
COM_WIND_WARN.long_desc: A warning is triggered if the currently estimated wind speed is above this value. Warning is sent periodically (every 1 minute).  Set to -1 to disable.

COM_FLT_TIME_MAX.name: COM_FLT_TIME_MAX
COM_FLT_TIME_MAX.long_desc: The vehicle aborts the current operation and returns to launch when the time since takeoff is above this value. It is not possible to resume the mission or switch to any auto mode other than RTL or Land. Taking over in any manual mode is still possible.  Starting from 90% of the maximum flight time, a warning message will be sent every 1 minute with the remaining time until automatic RTL.  Set to -1 to disable.

COM_WIND_MAX.name: COM_WIND_MAX
COM_WIND_MAX.long_desc: Wind speed threshold above which an automatic failsafe action is triggered. Failsafe action can be specified with COM_WIND_MAX_ACT.

COM_WIND_MAX_ACT.name: COM_WIND_MAX_ACT
COM_WIND_MAX_ACT.long_desc: Action the system takes when a wind speed above the specified threshold is detected. See COM_WIND_MAX to set the failsafe threshold. If enabled, it is not possible to resume the mission or switch to any auto mode other than RTL or Land if this threshold is exceeded. Taking over in any manual mode is still possible.

COM_POS_LOW_EPH.name: COM_POS_LOW_EPH
COM_POS_LOW_EPH.long_desc: This triggers the action specified in COM_POS_LOW_ACT if the estimated position accuracy is below this threshold. Local position has to be still declared valid, which requires some kind of velocity aiding or large dead-reckoning time (EKF2_NOAID_TOUT), and a high failsafe threshold (COM_POS_FS_EPH).  Set to -1 to disable.

COM_POS_LOW_ACT.name: COM_POS_LOW_ACT
COM_POS_LOW_ACT.long_desc: Action the system takes when the estimated position has an accuracy below the specified threshold. See COM_POS_LOW_EPH to set the failsafe threshold. The failsafe action is only executed if the vehicle is in auto mission or auto loiter mode, otherwise it is only a warning.

COM_ARMABLE.name: COM_ARMABLE
COM_ARMABLE.long_desc: Set 0 to prevent accidental use of the vehicle e.g. for safety or maintenance reasons.

COM_ARM_BAT_MIN.name: COM_ARM_BAT_MIN
COM_ARM_BAT_MIN.long_desc: Threshold for battery percentage below arming is prohibited.  A negative value means BAT_CRIT_THR is the threshold.

COM_THROW_EN.name: COM_THROW_EN
COM_THROW_EN.long_desc: Allows to start the vehicle by throwing it into the air.

COM_THROW_SPEED.name: COM_THROW_SPEED
COM_THROW_SPEED.short_desc: Minimum speed for the throw start
COM_THROW_SPEED.long_desc: When the throw launch is enabled, the drone will only allow motors to spin after this speed is exceeded before detecting the freefall. This is a safety feature to ensure the drone does not turn on after accidental drop or a rapid movement before the throw.  Set to 0 to disable.

COM_FLTT_LOW_ACT.name: COM_FLTT_LOW_ACT
COM_FLTT_LOW_ACT.long_desc: Action the system takes when the remaining flight time is below the estimated time it takes to reach the RTL destination.

COM_MODE_ARM_CHK.name: COM_MODE_ARM_CHK
COM_MODE_ARM_CHK.short_desc: Allow external mode registration while armed.
COM_MODE_ARM_CHK.long_desc: By default disabled for safety reasons

FD_FAIL_R.name: FD_FAIL_R
FD_FAIL_R.long_desc: Maximum roll angle before FailureDetector triggers the attitude_failure flag. which sets outputs to their failsafe values. which disarms motors but does not set outputs to failsafe values.  Setting this parameter to 0 disables the check

FD_FAIL_P.name: FD_FAIL_P
FD_FAIL_P.long_desc: Maximum pitch angle before FailureDetector triggers the attitude_failure flag. which sets outputs to their failsafe values. which disarms motors but does not set outputs to failsafe values.  Setting this parameter to 0 disables the check

FD_FAIL_R_TTRI.name: FD_FAIL_R_TTRI
FD_FAIL_R_TTRI.long_desc: Seconds (decimal) that roll has to exceed FD_FAIL_R before being considered as a failure.

FD_FAIL_P_TTRI.name: FD_FAIL_P_TTRI
FD_FAIL_P_TTRI.long_desc: Seconds (decimal) that pitch has to exceed FD_FAIL_P before being considered as a failure.

FD_EXT_ATS_EN.name: FD_EXT_ATS_EN
FD_EXT_ATS_EN.short_desc: Enable PWM input on for engaging failsafe from an external automatic trigger system (ATS).
FD_EXT_ATS_EN.long_desc: Enabled on either AUX5 or MAIN5 depending on board. External ATS is required by ASTM F3322-18.

FD_EXT_ATS_TRIG.name: FD_EXT_ATS_TRIG
FD_EXT_ATS_TRIG.short_desc: The PWM threshold from external automatic trigger system for engaging failsafe.
FD_EXT_ATS_TRIG.long_desc: External ATS is required by ASTM F3322-18.

FD_ESCS_EN.name: FD_ESCS_EN
FD_ESCS_EN.short_desc: Enable checks on ESCs that report their arming state.
FD_ESCS_EN.long_desc: If enabled, failure detector will verify that all the ESCs have successfully armed when the vehicle has transitioned to the armed state. Timeout for receiving an acknowledgement from the ESCs is 0.3s, if no feedback is received the failure detector will auto disarm the vehicle.

FD_IMB_PROP_THR.name: FD_IMB_PROP_THR
FD_IMB_PROP_THR.long_desc: Value at which the imbalanced propeller metric (based on horizontal and vertical acceleration variance) triggers a failure  Setting this value to 0 disables the feature.

FD_ACT_EN.name: FD_ACT_EN
FD_ACT_EN.long_desc: If enabled, failure detector will verify that for motors, a minimum amount of ESC current per throttle level is being consumed. Otherwise this indicates an motor failure.

FD_ACT_MOT_THR.name: FD_ACT_MOT_THR
FD_ACT_MOT_THR.long_desc: Motor failure triggers only above this throttle value.

FD_ACT_MOT_C2T.name: FD_ACT_MOT_C2T
FD_ACT_MOT_C2T.long_desc: Motor failure triggers only below this current value

FD_ACT_MOT_TOUT.name: FD_ACT_MOT_TOUT
FD_ACT_MOT_TOUT.long_desc: Motor failure triggers only if the throttle threshold and the current to throttle threshold are violated for this time.

EV_TSK_STAT_DIS.name: EV_TSK_STAT_DIS
EV_TSK_STAT_DIS.long_desc: Enable/disable event task for displaying the vehicle status using arm-mounted LEDs. When enabled and if the vehicle supports it, LEDs will flash indicating various vehicle status changes. Currently PX4 has not implemented any specific status events. -

EV_TSK_RC_LOSS.name: EV_TSK_RC_LOSS
EV_TSK_RC_LOSS.long_desc: Enable/disable event task for RC Loss. When enabled, an alarm tune will be played via buzzer or ESCs, if supported. The alarm will sound after a disarm, if the vehicle was previously armed and only if the vehicle had RC signal at some point. Particularly useful for locating crashed drones without a GPS sensor.

FLW_TGT_RS.name: FLW_TGT_RS
FLW_TGT_RS.short_desc: Responsiveness to target movement in Target Estimator
FLW_TGT_RS.long_desc: lower values increase the responsiveness to changing position, but also ignore less noise

FLW_TGT_DST.name: FLW_TGT_DST
FLW_TGT_DST.long_desc: The distance in meters to follow the target at

FLW_TGT_FA.name: FLW_TGT_FA
FLW_TGT_FA.long_desc: Angle to follow the target from. 0.0 Equals straight in front of the target's course (direction of motion) and the angle increases in clockwise direction, meaning Right-side would be 90.0 degrees while Left-side is -90.0 degrees  Note: When the user force sets the angle out of the min/max range, it will be wrapped (e.g. 480 -> 120) in the range to gracefully handle the out of range.

FLW_TGT_ALT_M.name: FLW_TGT_ALT_M
FLW_TGT_ALT_M.long_desc: Maintain altitude or track target's altitude. When maintaining the altitude, the drone can crash into terrain when the target moves uphill. When tracking the target's altitude, the follow altitude FLW_TGT_HT should be high enough to prevent terrain collisions due to GPS inaccuracies of the target.

FLW_TGT_MAX_VEL.name: FLW_TGT_MAX_VEL
FLW_TGT_MAX_VEL.short_desc: Maximum tangential velocity setting for generating the follow orbit trajectory
FLW_TGT_MAX_VEL.long_desc: This is the maximum tangential velocity the drone will circle around the target whenever an orbit angle setpoint changes. Higher value means more aggressive follow behavior.

MC_SLOW_MAP_HVEL.name: MC_SLOW_MAP_HVEL
MC_SLOW_MAP_HVEL.short_desc: Manual input mapped to scale horizontal velocity in position slow mode

MC_SLOW_MAP_VVEL.name: MC_SLOW_MAP_VVEL
MC_SLOW_MAP_VVEL.short_desc: Manual input mapped to scale vertical velocity in position slow mode

MC_SLOW_MAP_YAWR.name: MC_SLOW_MAP_YAWR
MC_SLOW_MAP_YAWR.short_desc: Manual input mapped to scale yaw rate in position slow mode

MC_SLOW_MIN_HVEL.name: MC_SLOW_MIN_HVEL
MC_SLOW_MIN_HVEL.long_desc: The lowest input maps and is clamped to this velocity.

MC_SLOW_MIN_VVEL.name: MC_SLOW_MIN_VVEL
MC_SLOW_MIN_VVEL.long_desc: The lowest input maps and is clamped to this velocity.

MC_SLOW_MIN_YAWR.name: MC_SLOW_MIN_YAWR
MC_SLOW_MIN_YAWR.long_desc: The lowest input maps and is clamped to this rate.

MC_SLOW_DEF_HVEL.name: MC_SLOW_DEF_HVEL
MC_SLOW_DEF_HVEL.long_desc: This value is used in slow mode if no aux channel is mapped and no limit is commanded through MAVLink.

MC_SLOW_DEF_VVEL.name: MC_SLOW_DEF_VVEL
MC_SLOW_DEF_VVEL.long_desc: This value is used in slow mode if no aux channel is mapped and no limit is commanded through MAVLink.

MC_SLOW_DEF_YAWR.name: MC_SLOW_DEF_YAWR
MC_SLOW_DEF_YAWR.long_desc: This value is used in slow mode if no aux channel is mapped and no limit is commanded through MAVLink.

FW_R_TC.name: FW_R_TC
FW_R_TC.long_desc: This defines the latency between a roll step input and the achieved setpoint (inverse to a P gain). Smaller systems may require smaller values.

FW_P_TC.name: FW_P_TC
FW_P_TC.long_desc: This defines the latency between a pitch step input and the achieved setpoint (inverse to a P gain). Smaller systems may require smaller values.

FW_P_RMAX_POS.name: FW_P_RMAX_POS
FW_P_RMAX_POS.short_desc: Maximum positive / up pitch rate setpoint

FW_P_RMAX_NEG.name: FW_P_RMAX_NEG
FW_P_RMAX_NEG.short_desc: Maximum negative / down pitch rate setpoint

FW_W_EN.name: FW_W_EN
FW_W_EN.long_desc: Only enabled during automatic runway takeoff and landing. In all manual modes the wheel is directly controlled with yaw stick.

FW_WR_P.name: FW_WR_P
FW_WR_P.long_desc: This defines how much the wheel steering input will be commanded depending on the current body angular rate error.

FW_WR_I.name: FW_WR_I
FW_WR_I.long_desc: This gain defines how much control response will result out of a steady state error. It trims any constant error.

FW_W_RMAX.name: FW_W_RMAX
FW_W_RMAX.long_desc: This limits the maximum wheel steering rate the controller will output (in degrees per second).

FW_PSP_OFF.name: FW_PSP_OFF
FW_PSP_OFF.short_desc: Pitch setpoint offset (pitch at level flight)
FW_PSP_OFF.long_desc: An airframe specific offset of the pitch setpoint in degrees, the value is added to the pitch setpoint and should correspond to the pitch at typical cruise speed of the airframe.

FW_MAN_YR_MAX.name: FW_MAN_YR_MAX
FW_MAN_YR_MAX.long_desc: This is the maximally added yaw rate setpoint from the yaw stick in any attitude controlled flight mode. It is added to the yaw rate setpoint generated by the controller for turn coordination.

FW_MAN_R_MAX.name: FW_MAN_R_MAX
FW_MAN_R_MAX.long_desc: Applies to both directions in all manual modes with attitude stabilization

FW_MAN_P_MAX.name: FW_MAN_P_MAX
FW_MAN_P_MAX.long_desc: Applies to both directions in all manual modes with attitude stabilization but without altitude control

FW_AT_START.name: FW_AT_START
FW_AT_START.long_desc: WARNING: this will inject steps to the rate controller and can be dangerous. Only activate if you know what you are doing, and in a safe environment.  Any motion of the remote stick will abort the signal injection and reset this parameter Best is to perform the identification in position or hold mode. Increase the amplitude of the injected signal using FW_AT_SYSID_AMP for more signal/noise ratio

FW_AT_SYSID_AMP.name: FW_AT_SYSID_AMP
FW_AT_SYSID_AMP.long_desc: This parameter scales the signal sent to the rate controller during system identification.

FW_AT_APPLY.name: FW_AT_APPLY
FW_AT_APPLY.short_desc: Controls when to apply the new gains
FW_AT_APPLY.long_desc: After the auto-tuning sequence is completed, a new set of gains is available and can be applied immediately or after landing.

FW_AT_AXES.name: FW_AT_AXES
FW_AT_AXES.long_desc: Defines which axes will be tuned during the auto-tuning sequence  Set bits in the following positions to enable: 0 : Roll 1 : Pitch 2 : Yaw

FW_AT_MAN_AUX.name: FW_AT_MAN_AUX
FW_AT_MAN_AUX.short_desc: Enable/disable auto tuning using an RC AUX input
FW_AT_MAN_AUX.long_desc: Defines which RC_MAP_AUXn parameter maps the RC channel used to enable/disable auto tuning.

FW_AT_SYSID_F0.name: FW_AT_SYSID_F0
FW_AT_SYSID_F0.short_desc: Start frequency of the injected signal
FW_AT_SYSID_F0.long_desc: Can be set lower or higher than the end frequency

FW_AT_SYSID_F1.name: FW_AT_SYSID_F1
FW_AT_SYSID_F1.short_desc: End frequency of the injected signal
FW_AT_SYSID_F1.long_desc: Can be set lower or higher than the start frequency

FW_AT_SYSID_TIME.name: FW_AT_SYSID_TIME
FW_AT_SYSID_TIME.long_desc: Duration of the input signal sent on each axis during system identification

FW_AT_SYSID_TYPE.name: FW_AT_SYSID_TYPE
FW_AT_SYSID_TYPE.long_desc: Type of signal used during system identification to excite the system.

FW_PN_R_SLEW_MAX.name: FW_PN_R_SLEW_MAX
FW_PN_R_SLEW_MAX.short_desc: Path navigation roll slew rate limit.
FW_PN_R_SLEW_MAX.long_desc: Maximum change in roll angle setpoint per second. Applied in all Auto modes, plus manual Position & Altitude modes.

NPFG_DAMPING.name: NPFG_DAMPING
NPFG_DAMPING.long_desc: Damping ratio of NPFG control law.

NPFG_LB_PERIOD.name: NPFG_LB_PERIOD
NPFG_LB_PERIOD.short_desc: Enable automatic lower bound on the NPFG period
NPFG_LB_PERIOD.long_desc: Avoids limit cycling from a too aggressively tuned period/damping combination. If false, also disables upper bound NPFG_PERIOD_UB.

NPFG_UB_PERIOD.name: NPFG_UB_PERIOD
NPFG_UB_PERIOD.short_desc: Enable automatic upper bound on the NPFG period
NPFG_UB_PERIOD.long_desc: Adapts period to maintain track keeping in variable winds and path curvature.

NPFG_TRACK_KEEP.name: NPFG_TRACK_KEEP
NPFG_TRACK_KEEP.short_desc: Enable track keeping excess wind handling logic.

NPFG_EN_MIN_GSP.name: NPFG_EN_MIN_GSP
NPFG_EN_MIN_GSP.short_desc: Enable minimum forward ground speed maintaining excess wind handling logic

NPFG_WIND_REG.name: NPFG_WIND_REG
NPFG_WIND_REG.long_desc: Disabling this parameter further disables all other airspeed incrementation options.

NPFG_GSP_MAX_TK.name: NPFG_GSP_MAX_TK
NPFG_GSP_MAX_TK.short_desc: Maximum, minimum forward ground speed for track keeping in excess wind
NPFG_GSP_MAX_TK.long_desc: The maximum value of the minimum forward ground speed that may be commanded by the track keeping excess wind handling logic. Commanded in full at the normalized track error fraction of the track error boundary and reduced to zero on track.

NPFG_ROLL_TC.name: NPFG_ROLL_TC
NPFG_ROLL_TC.long_desc: Time constant of roll controller command / response, modeled as first order delay. Used to determine lower period bound. Setting zero disables automatic period bounding.

NPFG_SW_DST_MLT.name: NPFG_SW_DST_MLT
NPFG_SW_DST_MLT.long_desc: Multiplied by the track error boundary to determine when the aircraft switches to the next waypoint and/or path segment. Should be less than 1.

NPFG_PERIOD_SF.name: NPFG_PERIOD_SF
NPFG_PERIOD_SF.long_desc: Multiplied by period for conservative minimum period bounding (when period lower bounding is enabled). 1.0 bounds at marginal stability.

FW_THR_SLEW_MAX.name: FW_THR_SLEW_MAX
FW_THR_SLEW_MAX.long_desc: Maximum slew rate for the commanded throttle

FW_P_LIM_MIN.name: FW_P_LIM_MIN
FW_P_LIM_MIN.long_desc: Applies in any altitude controlled flight mode.

FW_P_LIM_MAX.name: FW_P_LIM_MAX
FW_P_LIM_MAX.long_desc: Applies in any altitude controlled flight mode.

FW_R_LIM.name: FW_R_LIM
FW_R_LIM.long_desc: Applies in any altitude controlled flight mode.

FW_THR_MAX.name: FW_THR_MAX
FW_THR_MAX.long_desc: Applies in any altitude controlled flight mode. Should be set accordingly to achieve FW_T_CLMB_MAX.

FW_THR_MIN.name: FW_THR_MIN
FW_THR_MIN.long_desc: Applies in any altitude controlled flight mode. Usually set to 0 but can be increased to prevent the motor from stopping when descending, which can increase achievable descent rates.

FW_THR_IDLE.name: FW_THR_IDLE
FW_THR_IDLE.long_desc: This is the minimum throttle while on the ground ("landed") in auto modes.

FW_LND_ANG.name: FW_LND_ANG
FW_LND_ANG.long_desc: Typically the desired landing slope angle when landing configuration (flaps, airspeed) is enabled. Set this value within the vehicle's performance limits.

FW_TKO_AIRSPD.name: FW_TKO_AIRSPD
FW_TKO_AIRSPD.long_desc: The calibrated airspeed setpoint during the takeoff climbout.  If set <= 0, FW_AIRSPD_MIN will be set by default.

FW_LND_FLALT.name: FW_LND_FLALT
FW_LND_FLALT.short_desc: Landing flare altitude (relative to landing altitude)
FW_LND_FLALT.long_desc: NOTE: max(FW_LND_FLALT, FW_LND_FL_TIME * |z-velocity|) is taken as the flare altitude

FW_LND_USETER.name: FW_LND_USETER
FW_LND_USETER.long_desc: This is critical for detecting when to flare, and should be enabled if possible.  If enabled and no measurement is found within a given timeout, the landing waypoint altitude will be used OR the landing will be aborted, depending on the criteria set in FW_LND_ABORT.  If disabled, FW_LND_ABORT terrain based criteria are ignored.

FW_LND_EARLYCFG.name: FW_LND_EARLYCFG
FW_LND_EARLYCFG.long_desc: Allows to deploy the landing configuration (flaps, landing airspeed, etc.) already in the loiter-down waypoint before the final approach. Otherwise is enabled only in the final approach.

FW_LND_AIRSPD.name: FW_LND_AIRSPD
FW_LND_AIRSPD.long_desc: The calibrated airspeed setpoint during landing.  If set <= 0, landing airspeed = FW_AIRSPD_MIN by default.

FW_LND_THRTC_SC.name: FW_LND_THRTC_SC
FW_LND_THRTC_SC.short_desc: Altitude time constant factor for landing and low-height flight
FW_LND_THRTC_SC.long_desc: The TECS altitude time constant (FW_T_ALT_TC) is multiplied by this value.

FW_T_THR_LOW_HGT.name: FW_T_THR_LOW_HGT
FW_T_THR_LOW_HGT.short_desc: Low-height threshold for tighter altitude tracking
FW_T_THR_LOW_HGT.long_desc: Height above ground threshold below which tighter altitude tracking gets enabled (see FW_LND_THRTC_SC). Below this height, TECS smoothly (1 sec / sec) transitions the altitude tracking time constant from FW_T_ALT_TC to FW_LND_THRTC_SC*FW_T_ALT_TC.  -1 to disable.

FW_T_THR_DAMPING.name: FW_T_THR_DAMPING
FW_T_THR_DAMPING.long_desc: This is the damping gain for the throttle demand loop.

FW_T_THR_INTEG.name: FW_T_THR_INTEG
FW_T_THR_INTEG.long_desc: Increase it to trim out speed and height offsets faster, with the downside of possible overshoots and oscillations.

FW_T_I_GAIN_PIT.name: FW_T_I_GAIN_PIT
FW_T_I_GAIN_PIT.long_desc: Increase it to trim out speed and height offsets faster, with the downside of possible overshoots and oscillations.

FW_T_VERT_ACC.name: FW_T_VERT_ACC
FW_T_VERT_ACC.long_desc: This is the maximum vertical acceleration either up or down that the controller will use to correct speed or height errors.

FW_T_SPD_STD.name: FW_T_SPD_STD
FW_T_SPD_STD.long_desc: For the airspeed filter in TECS.

FW_T_SPD_DEV_STD.name: FW_T_SPD_DEV_STD
FW_T_SPD_DEV_STD.long_desc: For the airspeed filter in TECS.

FW_T_SPD_PRC_STD.name: FW_T_SPD_PRC_STD
FW_T_SPD_PRC_STD.short_desc: Process noise standard deviation for the airspeed rate
FW_T_SPD_PRC_STD.long_desc: This is defining the noise in the airspeed rate for the constant airspeed rate model of the TECS airspeed filter.

FW_T_RLL2THR.name: FW_T_RLL2THR
FW_T_RLL2THR.long_desc: Is used to compensate for the additional drag created by turning. Increase this gain if the aircraft initially loses energy in turns and reduce if the aircraft initially gains energy in turns.

FW_T_SPDWEIGHT.name: FW_T_SPDWEIGHT
FW_T_SPDWEIGHT.long_desc: Adjusts the amount of weighting that the pitch control applies to speed vs height errors. 0 -> control height only 2 -> control speed only (gliders)

FW_T_F_ALT_ERR.name: FW_T_F_ALT_ERR
FW_T_F_ALT_ERR.long_desc: Minimum altitude error needed to descend with max airspeed and minimal throttle. A negative value disables fast descend.

FW_GND_SPD_MIN.name: FW_GND_SPD_MIN
FW_GND_SPD_MIN.long_desc: The controller will increase the commanded airspeed to maintain this minimum groundspeed to the next waypoint.

FW_POS_STK_CONF.name: FW_POS_STK_CONF
FW_POS_STK_CONF.long_desc: Applies in manual Position and Altitude flight modes.

FW_T_STE_R_TC.name: FW_T_STE_R_TC
FW_T_STE_R_TC.short_desc: Specific total energy rate first order filter time constant.
FW_T_STE_R_TC.long_desc: This filter is applied to the specific total energy rate used for throttle damping.

FW_T_SEB_R_FF.name: FW_T_SEB_R_FF
FW_T_SEB_R_FF.short_desc: Specific total energy balance rate feedforward gain.

FW_T_CLMB_R_SP.name: FW_T_CLMB_R_SP
FW_T_CLMB_R_SP.long_desc: In auto modes: default climb rate output by controller to achieve altitude setpoints. In manual modes: maximum climb rate setpoint.

FW_T_SINK_R_SP.name: FW_T_SINK_R_SP
FW_T_SINK_R_SP.long_desc: In auto modes: default sink rate output by controller to achieve altitude setpoints. In manual modes: maximum sink rate setpoint.

FW_GPSF_LT.name: FW_GPSF_LT
FW_GPSF_LT.long_desc: The time the system should do open loop loiter and wait for GPS recovery before it starts descending. Set to 0 to disable. Roll angle is set to FW_GPSF_R. Does only apply for fixed-wing vehicles or VTOLs with NAV_FORCE_VT set to 0.

FW_GPSF_R.name: FW_GPSF_R
FW_GPSF_R.long_desc: Roll angle in GPS failure loiter mode.

FW_WING_SPAN.name: FW_WING_SPAN
FW_WING_SPAN.short_desc: The aircraft's wing span (length from tip to tip).
FW_WING_SPAN.long_desc: This is used for limiting the roll setpoint near the ground. (if multiple wings, take the longest span)

FW_WING_HEIGHT.name: FW_WING_HEIGHT
FW_WING_HEIGHT.short_desc: Height (AGL) of the wings when the aircraft is on the ground.
FW_WING_HEIGHT.long_desc: This is used to constrain a minimum altitude below which we keep wings level to avoid wing tip strike. It's safer to give a slight margin here (> 0m)

FW_LND_FL_TIME.name: FW_LND_FL_TIME
FW_LND_FL_TIME.long_desc: Multiplied by the descent rate to calculate a dynamic altitude at which to trigger the flare.  NOTE: max(FW_LND_FLALT, FW_LND_FL_TIME * descent rate) is taken as the flare altitude

FW_LND_TD_TIME.name: FW_LND_TD_TIME
FW_LND_TD_TIME.long_desc: This is the time after the start of flaring that we expect the vehicle to touch the runway. At this time, a 0.5s clamp down ramp will engage, constraining the pitch setpoint to RWTO_PSP. If enabled, ensure that RWTO_PSP is configured appropriately for full gear contact on ground roll.  Set to -1.0 to disable touchdown clamping. E.g. it may not be desirable to clamp on belly landings.  The touchdown time will be constrained to be greater than or equal to the flare time (FW_LND_FL_TIME).

FW_LND_FL_SINK.name: FW_LND_FL_SINK
FW_LND_FL_SINK.long_desc: TECS will attempt to control the aircraft to this sink rate via pitch angle (throttle killed during flare)

FW_LND_TD_OFF.name: FW_LND_TD_OFF
FW_LND_TD_OFF.short_desc: Maximum lateral position offset for the touchdown point

FW_LND_NUDGE.name: FW_LND_NUDGE
FW_LND_NUDGE.long_desc: Approach angle nudging: shifts the touchdown point laterally while keeping the approach entrance point constant Approach path nudging: shifts the touchdown point laterally along with the entire approach path  This is useful for manually adjusting the landing point in real time when map or GNSS errors cause an offset from the desired landing vector. Nudging is done with yaw stick, constrained to FW_LND_TD_OFF (in meters) and the direction is relative to the vehicle heading (stick deflection to the right = land point moves to the right as seen by the vehicle).

FW_LND_ABORT.name: FW_LND_ABORT
FW_LND_ABORT.short_desc: Bit mask to set the automatic landing abort conditions.
FW_LND_ABORT.long_desc: Terrain estimation: bit 0: Abort if terrain is not found bit 1: Abort if terrain times out (after a first successful measurement)  The last estimate is always used as ground, whether the last valid measurement or the land waypoint, depending on the selected abort criteria, until an abort condition is entered. If FW_LND_USETER == 0, these bits are ignored.  TODO: Extend automatic abort conditions e.g. glide slope tracking error (horizontal and vertical)

FW_WIND_ARSP_SC.name: FW_WIND_ARSP_SC
FW_WIND_ARSP_SC.long_desc: Multiplying this factor with the current absolute wind estimate gives the airspeed offset added to the minimum airspeed setpoint limit. This helps to make the system more robust against disturbances (turbulence) in high wind.

FW_LAUN_DETCN_ON.name: FW_LAUN_DETCN_ON
FW_LAUN_DETCN_ON.long_desc: Enables automatic launch detection based on measured acceleration. Use for hand- or catapult-launched vehicles. Not compatible with runway takeoff.

FW_FLAPS_TO_SCL.name: FW_FLAPS_TO_SCL
FW_FLAPS_TO_SCL.long_desc: Sets a fraction of full flaps during take-off. Also applies to flaperons if enabled in the mixer/allocation.

FW_FLAPS_LND_SCL.name: FW_FLAPS_LND_SCL
FW_FLAPS_LND_SCL.long_desc: Sets a fraction of full flaps during landing. Also applies to flaperons if enabled in the mixer/allocation.

FW_LAUN_AC_THLD.name: FW_LAUN_AC_THLD
FW_LAUN_AC_THLD.long_desc: Launch is detected when acceleration in body forward direction is above FW_LAUN_AC_THLD for FW_LAUN_AC_T seconds.

FW_LAUN_AC_T.name: FW_LAUN_AC_T
FW_LAUN_AC_T.long_desc: Launch is detected when acceleration in body forward direction is above FW_LAUN_AC_THLD for FW_LAUN_AC_T seconds.

FW_LAUN_MOT_DEL.name: FW_LAUN_MOT_DEL
FW_LAUN_MOT_DEL.long_desc: Start the motor(s) this amount of seconds after launch is detected.

RWTO_HDG.name: RWTO_HDG
RWTO_HDG.short_desc: Specifies which heading should be held during the runway takeoff ground roll.
RWTO_HDG.long_desc: 0: airframe heading when takeoff is initiated 1: position control along runway direction (bearing defined from vehicle position on takeoff initiation to MAV_CMD_TAKEOFF position defined by operator)

RWTO_PSP.name: RWTO_PSP
RWTO_PSP.short_desc: Pitch setpoint during taxi / before takeoff rotation airspeed is reached.
RWTO_PSP.long_desc: A taildragger with steerable wheel might need to pitch up a little to keep its wheel on the ground before airspeed to takeoff is reached.

RWTO_RAMP_TIME.name: RWTO_RAMP_TIME
RWTO_RAMP_TIME.short_desc: Throttle ramp up time for runway takeoff

RWTO_NPFG_PERIOD.name: RWTO_NPFG_PERIOD
RWTO_NPFG_PERIOD.short_desc: NPFG period while steering on runway

RWTO_NUDGE.name: RWTO_NUDGE
RWTO_NUDGE.short_desc: Enable use of yaw stick for nudging the wheel during runway ground roll
RWTO_NUDGE.long_desc: This is useful when map, GNSS, or yaw errors on ground are misaligned with what the operator intends for takeoff course. Particularly useful for skinny runways or if the wheel servo is a bit off trim.

RWTO_ROT_AIRSPD.name: RWTO_ROT_AIRSPD
RWTO_ROT_AIRSPD.long_desc: The calibrated airspeed threshold during the takeoff ground roll when the plane should start rotating (pitching up). Must be less than the takeoff airspeed, will otherwise be capped at the takeoff airpeed (see FW_TKO_AIRSPD).  If set <= 0.0, defaults to 0.9 * takeoff airspeed (see FW_TKO_AIRSPD)

RWTO_ROT_TIME.name: RWTO_ROT_TIME
RWTO_ROT_TIME.long_desc: This is the time desired to linearly ramp in takeoff pitch constraints during the takeoff rotation

FW_USE_AIRSPD.name: FW_USE_AIRSPD
FW_USE_AIRSPD.long_desc: If set to 1, the airspeed measurement data, if valid, is used in the following controllers: - Rate controller: output scaling - Attitude controller: coordinated turn controller - Position controller: airspeed setpoint tracking, takeoff logic - VTOL: transition logic

FW_RR_FF.name: FW_RR_FF
FW_RR_FF.long_desc: Direct feed forward from rate setpoint to control surface output.

FW_PR_FF.name: FW_PR_FF
FW_PR_FF.long_desc: Direct feed forward from rate setpoint to control surface output

FW_YR_FF.name: FW_YR_FF
FW_YR_FF.long_desc: Direct feed forward from rate setpoint to control surface output

FW_ACRO_X_MAX.name: FW_ACRO_X_MAX
FW_ACRO_X_MAX.short_desc: Acro body roll max rate setpoint

FW_ACRO_Y_MAX.name: FW_ACRO_Y_MAX
FW_ACRO_Y_MAX.short_desc: Acro body pitch max rate setpoint

FW_ACRO_Z_MAX.name: FW_ACRO_Z_MAX
FW_ACRO_Z_MAX.short_desc: Acro body yaw max rate setpoint

FW_BAT_SCALE_EN.name: FW_BAT_SCALE_EN
FW_BAT_SCALE_EN.short_desc: Enable throttle scale by battery level
FW_BAT_SCALE_EN.long_desc: This compensates for voltage drop of the battery over time by attempting to normalize performance across the operating range of the battery.

FW_ARSP_SCALE_EN.name: FW_ARSP_SCALE_EN
FW_ARSP_SCALE_EN.long_desc: This enables a logic that automatically adjusts the output of the rate controller to take into account the real torque produced by an aerodynamic control surface given the current deviation from the trim airspeed (FW_AIRSPD_TRIM).  Enable when using aerodynamic control surfaces (e.g.: plane) Disable when using rotor wings (e.g.: autogyro)

FW_DTRIM_R_VMIN.name: FW_DTRIM_R_VMIN
FW_DTRIM_R_VMIN.short_desc: Roll trim increment at minimum airspeed
FW_DTRIM_R_VMIN.long_desc: This increment is added to TRIM_ROLL when airspeed is FW_AIRSPD_MIN.

FW_DTRIM_P_VMIN.name: FW_DTRIM_P_VMIN
FW_DTRIM_P_VMIN.short_desc: Pitch trim increment at minimum airspeed
FW_DTRIM_P_VMIN.long_desc: This increment is added to TRIM_PITCH when airspeed is FW_AIRSPD_MIN.

FW_DTRIM_Y_VMIN.name: FW_DTRIM_Y_VMIN
FW_DTRIM_Y_VMIN.short_desc: Yaw trim increment at minimum airspeed
FW_DTRIM_Y_VMIN.long_desc: This increment is added to TRIM_YAW when airspeed is FW_AIRSPD_MIN.

FW_DTRIM_R_VMAX.name: FW_DTRIM_R_VMAX
FW_DTRIM_R_VMAX.short_desc: Roll trim increment at maximum airspeed
FW_DTRIM_R_VMAX.long_desc: This increment is added to TRIM_ROLL when airspeed is FW_AIRSPD_MAX.

FW_DTRIM_P_VMAX.name: FW_DTRIM_P_VMAX
FW_DTRIM_P_VMAX.short_desc: Pitch trim increment at maximum airspeed
FW_DTRIM_P_VMAX.long_desc: This increment is added to TRIM_PITCH when airspeed is FW_AIRSPD_MAX.

FW_DTRIM_Y_VMAX.name: FW_DTRIM_Y_VMAX
FW_DTRIM_Y_VMAX.short_desc: Yaw trim increment at maximum airspeed
FW_DTRIM_Y_VMAX.long_desc: This increment is added to TRIM_YAW when airspeed is FW_AIRSPD_MAX.

FW_MAN_R_SC.name: FW_MAN_R_SC
FW_MAN_R_SC.long_desc: Scale factor applied to the desired roll actuator command in full manual mode. This parameter allows to adjust the throws of the control surfaces.

FW_MAN_P_SC.name: FW_MAN_P_SC
FW_MAN_P_SC.long_desc: Scale factor applied to the desired pitch actuator command in full manual mode. This parameter allows to adjust the throws of the control surfaces.

FW_MAN_Y_SC.name: FW_MAN_Y_SC
FW_MAN_Y_SC.long_desc: Scale factor applied to the desired yaw actuator command in full manual mode. This parameter allows to adjust the throws of the control surfaces.

FW_RLL_TO_YAW_FF.name: FW_RLL_TO_YAW_FF
FW_RLL_TO_YAW_FF.short_desc: Roll control to yaw control feedforward gain.
FW_RLL_TO_YAW_FF.long_desc: This gain can be used to counteract the "adverse yaw" effect for fixed wings. When the plane enters a roll it will tend to yaw the nose out of the turn. This gain enables the use of a yaw actuator to counteract this effect.

FW_SPOILERS_MAN.name: FW_SPOILERS_MAN
FW_SPOILERS_MAN.long_desc: Chose source for manual setting of spoilers in manual flight modes.

FW_ACRO_YAW_EN.name: FW_ACRO_YAW_EN
FW_ACRO_YAW_EN.short_desc: Enable yaw rate controller in Acro
FW_ACRO_YAW_EN.long_desc: If this parameter is set to 1, the yaw rate controller is enabled in Fixed-wing Acro mode. Otherwise the pilot commands directly the yaw actuator. It is disabled by default because an active yaw rate controller will fight against the natural turn coordination of the plane.

MNT_MODE_IN.name: MNT_MODE_IN
MNT_MODE_IN.long_desc: This is the protocol used between the ground station and the autopilot.  Recommended is Auto, RC only or MAVLink gimbal protocol v2. The rest will be deprecated.

MNT_MODE_OUT.name: MNT_MODE_OUT
MNT_MODE_OUT.long_desc: This is the protocol used between the autopilot and a connected gimbal.  Recommended is the MAVLink gimbal protocol v2 if the gimbal supports it.

MNT_MAV_SYSID.name: MNT_MAV_SYSID
MNT_MAV_SYSID.short_desc: Mavlink System ID of the mount
MNT_MAV_SYSID.long_desc: If MNT_MODE_OUT is MAVLink gimbal protocol v1, mount configure/control commands will be sent with this target ID.

MNT_MAV_COMPID.name: MNT_MAV_COMPID
MNT_MAV_COMPID.short_desc: Mavlink Component ID of the mount
MNT_MAV_COMPID.long_desc: If MNT_MODE_OUT is MAVLink protocol v2, mount configure/control commands will be sent with this component ID.

MNT_MAN_ROLL.name: MNT_MAN_ROLL
MNT_MAN_ROLL.short_desc: Auxiliary channel to control roll (in AUX input or manual mode).

MNT_MAN_PITCH.name: MNT_MAN_PITCH
MNT_MAN_PITCH.short_desc: Auxiliary channel to control pitch (in AUX input or manual mode).

MNT_MAN_YAW.name: MNT_MAN_YAW
MNT_MAN_YAW.short_desc: Auxiliary channel to control yaw (in AUX input or manual mode).

MNT_DO_STAB.name: MNT_DO_STAB
MNT_DO_STAB.long_desc: Set to true for servo gimbal, false for passthrough. This is required for a gimbal which is not capable of stabilizing itself and relies on the IMU's attitude estimation.

MNT_RANGE_PITCH.name: MNT_RANGE_PITCH
MNT_RANGE_PITCH.short_desc: Range of pitch channel output in degrees (only in AUX output mode).

MNT_RANGE_ROLL.name: MNT_RANGE_ROLL
MNT_RANGE_ROLL.short_desc: Range of roll channel output in degrees (only in AUX output mode).

MNT_RANGE_YAW.name: MNT_RANGE_YAW
MNT_RANGE_YAW.short_desc: Range of yaw channel output in degrees (only in AUX output mode).

MNT_OFF_PITCH.name: MNT_OFF_PITCH
MNT_OFF_PITCH.short_desc: Offset for pitch channel output in degrees.

MNT_OFF_ROLL.name: MNT_OFF_ROLL
MNT_OFF_ROLL.short_desc: Offset for roll channel output in degrees.

MNT_OFF_YAW.name: MNT_OFF_YAW
MNT_OFF_YAW.short_desc: Offset for yaw channel output in degrees.

MNT_RATE_PITCH.name: MNT_RATE_PITCH
MNT_RATE_PITCH.short_desc: Angular pitch rate for manual input in degrees/second.
MNT_RATE_PITCH.long_desc: Full stick input [-1..1] translats to [-pitch rate..pitch rate].

MNT_RATE_YAW.name: MNT_RATE_YAW
MNT_RATE_YAW.short_desc: Angular yaw rate for manual input in degrees/second.
MNT_RATE_YAW.long_desc: Full stick input [-1..1] translats to [-yaw rate..yaw rate].

MNT_RC_IN_MODE.name: MNT_RC_IN_MODE
MNT_RC_IN_MODE.short_desc: Input mode for RC gimbal input

LTEST_MODE.name: LTEST_MODE
LTEST_MODE.long_desc: Configure the mode of the landing target. Depending on the mode, the landing target observations are used differently to aid position estimation.  Mode Moving:     The landing target may be moving around while in the field of view of the vehicle. Landing target measurements are not used to aid positioning. Mode Stationary: The landing target is stationary. Measured velocity w.r.t. the landing target is used to aid velocity estimation.

LTEST_ACC_UNC.name: LTEST_ACC_UNC
LTEST_ACC_UNC.long_desc: Variance of acceleration measurement used for landing target position prediction. Higher values results in tighter following of the measurements and more lenient outlier rejection

LTEST_MEAS_UNC.name: LTEST_MEAS_UNC
LTEST_MEAS_UNC.long_desc: Variance of the landing target measurement from the driver. Higher values result in less aggressive following of the measurement and a smoother output as well as fewer rejected measurements.

LTEST_POS_UNC_IN.name: LTEST_POS_UNC_IN
LTEST_POS_UNC_IN.long_desc: Initial variance of the relative landing target position in x and y direction

LTEST_VEL_UNC_IN.name: LTEST_VEL_UNC_IN
LTEST_VEL_UNC_IN.long_desc: Initial variance of the relative landing target velocity in x and y directions

LTEST_SCALE_X.name: LTEST_SCALE_X
LTEST_SCALE_X.short_desc: Scale factor for sensor measurements in sensor x axis
LTEST_SCALE_X.long_desc: Landing target x measurements are scaled by this factor before being used

LTEST_SCALE_Y.name: LTEST_SCALE_Y
LTEST_SCALE_Y.short_desc: Scale factor for sensor measurements in sensor y axis
LTEST_SCALE_Y.long_desc: Landing target y measurements are scaled by this factor before being used

LTEST_SENS_ROT.name: LTEST_SENS_ROT
LTEST_SENS_ROT.short_desc: Rotation of IRLOCK sensor relative to airframe

LTEST_SENS_POS_X.name: LTEST_SENS_POS_X
