LTEST_SENS_POS_X.short_desc: X Position of IRLOCK in body frame (forward)

LTEST_SENS_POS_Y.name: LTEST_SENS_POS_Y
LTEST_SENS_POS_Y.short_desc: Y Position of IRLOCK in body frame (right)

LTEST_SENS_POS_Z.name: LTEST_SENS_POS_Z
LTEST_SENS_POS_Z.short_desc: Z Position of IRLOCK in body frame (downward)

LND_FLIGHT_T_HI.name: LND_FLIGHT_T_HI
LND_FLIGHT_T_HI.long_desc: Total flight time of this autopilot. Higher 32 bits of the value. Flight time in microseconds = (LND_FLIGHT_T_HI << 32) | LND_FLIGHT_T_LO.

LND_FLIGHT_T_LO.name: LND_FLIGHT_T_LO
LND_FLIGHT_T_LO.long_desc: Total flight time of this autopilot. Lower 32 bits of the value. Flight time in microseconds = (LND_FLIGHT_T_HI << 32) | LND_FLIGHT_T_LO.

LNDFW_VEL_XY_MAX.name: LNDFW_VEL_XY_MAX
LNDFW_VEL_XY_MAX.short_desc: Fixed-wing land detector: Max horizontal velocity threshold
LNDFW_VEL_XY_MAX.long_desc: Maximum horizontal velocity allowed in the landed state. A factor of 0.7 is applied in case of airspeed-less flying (either because no sensor is present or sensor data got invalid in flight).

LNDFW_VEL_Z_MAX.name: LNDFW_VEL_Z_MAX
LNDFW_VEL_Z_MAX.short_desc: Fixed-wing land detector: Max vertiacal velocity threshold
LNDFW_VEL_Z_MAX.long_desc: Maximum vertical velocity allowed in the landed state.

LNDFW_XYACC_MAX.name: LNDFW_XYACC_MAX
LNDFW_XYACC_MAX.short_desc: Fixed-wing land detector: Max horizontal acceleration
LNDFW_XYACC_MAX.long_desc: Maximum horizontal (x,y body axes) acceleration allowed in the landed state

LNDFW_AIRSPD_MAX.name: LNDFW_AIRSPD_MAX
LNDFW_AIRSPD_MAX.long_desc: Maximum airspeed allowed in the landed state

LNDFW_TRIG_TIME.name: LNDFW_TRIG_TIME
LNDFW_TRIG_TIME.long_desc: Time the land conditions (speeds and acceleration) have to be satisfied to detect a landing.

LNDFW_ROT_MAX.name: LNDFW_ROT_MAX
LNDFW_ROT_MAX.short_desc: Fixed-wing land detector: max rotational speed
LNDFW_ROT_MAX.long_desc: Maximum allowed norm of the angular velocity in the landed state.

LNDMC_TRIG_TIME.name: LNDMC_TRIG_TIME
LNDMC_TRIG_TIME.long_desc: Total time it takes to go through all three land detection stages: ground contact, maybe landed, landed when all necessary conditions are constantly met.

LNDMC_Z_VEL_MAX.name: LNDMC_Z_VEL_MAX
LNDMC_Z_VEL_MAX.long_desc: Vertical velocity threshold to detect landing. Has to be set lower than the expected minimal speed for landing, which is either MPC_LAND_SPEED or MPC_LAND_CRWL. This is enforced by an automatic check.

LNDMC_XY_VEL_MAX.name: LNDMC_XY_VEL_MAX
LNDMC_XY_VEL_MAX.long_desc: Maximum horizontal velocity allowed in the landed state

LNDMC_ROT_MAX.name: LNDMC_ROT_MAX
LNDMC_ROT_MAX.long_desc: Maximum allowed norm of the angular velocity (roll, pitch) in the landed state.

LNDMC_ALT_GND.name: LNDMC_ALT_GND
LNDMC_ALT_GND.long_desc: The height above ground below which ground effect creates barometric altitude errors. A negative value indicates no ground effect.

LPE_FLW_OFF_Z.name: LPE_FLW_OFF_Z
LPE_FLW_OFF_Z.short_desc: Optical flow z offset from center

LPE_FLW_RR.name: LPE_FLW_RR
LPE_FLW_RR.short_desc: Optical flow angular velocity noise gain

LPE_SNR_OFF_Z.name: LPE_SNR_OFF_Z
LPE_SNR_OFF_Z.short_desc: Sonar z offset from center of vehicle +down

LPE_LDR_OFF_Z.name: LPE_LDR_OFF_Z
LPE_LDR_OFF_Z.short_desc: Lidar z offset from center of vehicle +down

LPE_ACC_XY.name: LPE_ACC_XY
LPE_ACC_XY.long_desc: Data sheet noise density = 150ug/sqrt(Hz) = 0.0015 m/s^2/sqrt(Hz)  Larger than data sheet to account for tilt error.

LPE_BAR_Z.name: LPE_BAR_Z
LPE_BAR_Z.short_desc: Barometric presssure altitude z standard deviation.

LPE_GPS_XY.name: LPE_GPS_XY
LPE_GPS_XY.short_desc: Minimum GPS xy standard deviation, uses reported EPH if greater.

LPE_GPS_Z.name: LPE_GPS_Z
LPE_GPS_Z.short_desc: Minimum GPS z standard deviation, uses reported EPV if greater.

LPE_GPS_VXY.name: LPE_GPS_VXY
LPE_GPS_VXY.long_desc: EPV used if greater than this value.

LPE_EPH_MAX.name: LPE_EPH_MAX
LPE_EPH_MAX.short_desc: Max EPH allowed for GPS initialization

LPE_EPV_MAX.name: LPE_EPV_MAX
LPE_EPV_MAX.short_desc: Max EPV allowed for GPS initialization

LPE_VIS_DELAY.name: LPE_VIS_DELAY
LPE_VIS_DELAY.long_desc: Set to zero to enable automatic compensation from measurement timestamps

LPE_PN_P.name: LPE_PN_P
LPE_PN_P.long_desc: Increase to trust measurements more. Decrease to trust model more.

LPE_PN_V.name: LPE_PN_V
LPE_PN_V.long_desc: Increase to trust measurements more. Decrease to trust model more.

LPE_PN_T.name: LPE_PN_T
LPE_PN_T.short_desc: Terrain random walk noise density, hilly/outdoor (0.1), flat/Indoor (0.001)

LPE_T_MAX_GRADE.name: LPE_T_MAX_GRADE
LPE_T_MAX_GRADE.short_desc: Terrain maximum percent grade, hilly/outdoor (100 = 45 deg), flat/Indoor (0 = 0 deg)
LPE_T_MAX_GRADE.long_desc: Used to calculate increased terrain random walk nosie due to movement.

LPE_FGYRO_HP.name: LPE_FGYRO_HP
LPE_FGYRO_HP.short_desc: Flow gyro high pass filter cut off frequency

LPE_FAKE_ORIGIN.name: LPE_FAKE_ORIGIN
LPE_FAKE_ORIGIN.short_desc: Enable publishing of a fake global position (e.g for AUTO missions using Optical Flow)
LPE_FAKE_ORIGIN.long_desc: By initializing the estimator to the LPE_LAT/LON parameters when global information is unavailable

LPE_LAT.name: LPE_LAT
LPE_LAT.short_desc: Local origin latitude for nav w/o GPS

LPE_LON.name: LPE_LON
LPE_LON.short_desc: Local origin longitude for nav w/o GPS

LPE_VXY_PUB.name: LPE_VXY_PUB
LPE_VXY_PUB.short_desc: Required velocity xy standard deviation to publish position

LPE_Z_PUB.name: LPE_Z_PUB
LPE_Z_PUB.short_desc: Required z standard deviation to publish altitude/ terrain

LPE_LAND_VXY.name: LPE_LAND_VXY
LPE_LAND_VXY.short_desc: Land detector xy velocity standard deviation

LPE_LT_COV.name: LPE_LT_COV
LPE_LT_COV.short_desc: Minimum landing target standard covariance, uses reported covariance if greater.

LPE_FUSION.name: LPE_FUSION
LPE_FUSION.long_desc: Set bits in the following positions to enable: 0 : Set to true to fuse GPS data if available, also requires GPS for altitude init 1 : Set to true to fuse optical flow data if available 2 : Set to true to fuse vision position 3 : Set to true to enable landing target 4 : Set to true to fuse land detector 5 : Set to true to publish AGL as local position down component 6 : Set to true to enable flow gyro compensation 7 : Set to true to enable baro fusion  default (145 - GPS, baro, land detector)

SDLOG_UTC_OFFSET.name: SDLOG_UTC_OFFSET
SDLOG_UTC_OFFSET.long_desc: the difference in hours and minutes from Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) for a your place and date.  for example, In case of South Korea(UTC+09:00), UTC offset is 540 min (9*60)  refer to https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_UTC_time_offsets

SDLOG_MODE.name: SDLOG_MODE
SDLOG_MODE.long_desc: Determines when to start and stop logging. By default, logging is started when arming the system, and stopped when disarming.

SDLOG_BOOT_BAT.name: SDLOG_BOOT_BAT
SDLOG_BOOT_BAT.long_desc: When enabled, logging will not start from boot if battery power is not detected (e.g. powered via USB on a test bench). This prevents extraneous flight logs from being created during bench testing.  Note that this only applies to log-from-boot modes. This has no effect on arm-based modes.

SDLOG_MISSION.name: SDLOG_MISSION
SDLOG_MISSION.long_desc: If enabled, a small additional "mission" log file will be written to the SD card. The log contains just those messages that are useful for tasks like generating flight statistics and geotagging.  The different modes can be used to further reduce the logged data (and thus the log file size). For example, choose geotagging mode to only log data required for geotagging.  Note that the normal/full log is still created, and contains all the data in the mission log (and more).

SDLOG_PROFILE.name: SDLOG_PROFILE
SDLOG_PROFILE.long_desc: This integer bitmask controls the set and rates of logged topics. The default allows for general log analysis while keeping the log file size reasonably small.  Enabling multiple sets leads to higher bandwidth requirements and larger log files.  Set bits true to enable: 0 : Default set (used for general log analysis) 1 : Full rate estimator (EKF2) replay topics 2 : Topics for thermal calibration (high rate raw IMU and Baro sensor data) 3 : Topics for system identification (high rate actuator control and IMU data) 4 : Full rates for analysis of fast maneuvers (RC, attitude, rates and actuators) 5 : Debugging topics (debug_*.msg topics, for custom code) 6 : Topics for sensor comparison (low rate raw IMU, Baro and magnetometer data) 7 : Topics for computer vision and collision avoidance 8 : Raw FIFO high-rate IMU (Gyro) 9 : Raw FIFO high-rate IMU (Accel) 10: Logging of mavlink tunnel message (useful for payload communication debugging)

SDLOG_DIRS_MAX.name: SDLOG_DIRS_MAX
SDLOG_DIRS_MAX.short_desc: Maximum number of log directories to keep
SDLOG_DIRS_MAX.long_desc: If there are more log directories than this value, the system will delete the oldest directories during startup.  In addition, the system will delete old logs if there is not enough free space left. The minimum amount is 300 MB.  If this is set to 0, old directories will only be removed if the free space falls below the minimum.  Note: this does not apply to mission log files.

SDLOG_UUID.name: SDLOG_UUID
SDLOG_UUID.long_desc: If set to 1, add an ID to the log, which uniquely identifies the vehicle

SDLOG_ALGORITHM.name: SDLOG_ALGORITHM
SDLOG_ALGORITHM.long_desc: Selects the algorithm used for logfile encryption

SDLOG_KEY.name: SDLOG_KEY
SDLOG_KEY.long_desc: Selects the key in keystore, used for encrypting the log. When using a symmetric encryption algorithm, the key is generated at logging start and kept stored in this index. For symmetric algorithms, the key is volatile and valid only for the duration of logging. The key is stored in encrypted format on the sdcard alongside the logfile, using an RSA2048 key defined by the SDLOG_EXCHANGE_KEY

SDLOG_EXCH_KEY.name: SDLOG_EXCH_KEY
SDLOG_EXCH_KEY.long_desc: If the logfile is encrypted using a symmetric key algorithm, the used encryption key is generated at logging start and stored on the sdcard RSA2048 encrypted using this key.

MBE_ENABLE.name: MBE_ENABLE
MBE_ENABLE.long_desc: This enables continuous calibration of the magnetometers before takeoff using gyro data.

MBE_LEARN_GAIN.name: MBE_LEARN_GAIN
MBE_LEARN_GAIN.long_desc: Increase to make the estimator more responsive Decrease to make the estimator more robust to noise

MAN_ARM_GESTURE.name: MAN_ARM_GESTURE
MAN_ARM_GESTURE.long_desc: This determines if moving the left stick to the lower right arms and to the lower left disarms the vehicle.

MAN_KILL_GEST_T.name: MAN_KILL_GEST_T
MAN_KILL_GEST_T.short_desc: Trigger time for kill stick gesture
MAN_KILL_GEST_T.long_desc: The timeout for holding the left stick to the lower left and the right stick to the lower right at the same time until the gesture kills the actuators one-way.  A negative value disables the feature.

MAV_SIK_RADIO_ID.name: MAV_SIK_RADIO_ID
MAV_SIK_RADIO_ID.long_desc: When non-zero the MAVLink app will attempt to configure the SiK radio to this ID and re-set the parameter to 0. If the value is negative it will reset the complete radio config to factory defaults. Only applies if this mavlink instance is going through a SiK radio

MAV_USEHILGPS.name: MAV_USEHILGPS
MAV_USEHILGPS.short_desc: Use/Accept HIL GPS message even if not in HIL mode
MAV_USEHILGPS.long_desc: If set to 1 incoming HIL GPS messages are parsed.

MAV_FWDEXTSP.name: MAV_FWDEXTSP
MAV_FWDEXTSP.long_desc: If set to 1 incoming external setpoint messages will be directly forwarded to the controllers if in offboard control mode

MAV_HASH_CHK_EN.name: MAV_HASH_CHK_EN
MAV_HASH_CHK_EN.long_desc: Disabling the parameter hash check functionality will make the mavlink instance stream parameters continuously.

MAV_HB_FORW_EN.name: MAV_HB_FORW_EN
MAV_HB_FORW_EN.long_desc: The mavlink heartbeat message will not be forwarded if this parameter is set to 'disabled'. The main reason for disabling heartbeats to be forwarded is because they confuse dronekit.

MAV_RADIO_TOUT.name: MAV_RADIO_TOUT
MAV_RADIO_TOUT.short_desc: Timeout in seconds for the RADIO_STATUS reports coming in
MAV_RADIO_TOUT.long_desc: If the connected radio stops reporting RADIO_STATUS for a certain time, a warning is triggered and, if MAV_X_RADIO_CTL is enabled, the software-flow control is reset.

MC_ROLL_P.name: MC_ROLL_P
MC_ROLL_P.long_desc: Roll proportional gain, i.e. desired angular speed in rad/s for error 1 rad.

MC_PITCH_P.name: MC_PITCH_P
MC_PITCH_P.long_desc: Pitch proportional gain, i.e. desired angular speed in rad/s for error 1 rad.

MC_YAW_P.name: MC_YAW_P
MC_YAW_P.long_desc: Yaw proportional gain, i.e. desired angular speed in rad/s for error 1 rad.

MC_YAW_WEIGHT.name: MC_YAW_WEIGHT
MC_YAW_WEIGHT.long_desc: A fraction [0,1] deprioritizing yaw compared to roll and pitch in non-linear attitude control. Deprioritizing yaw is necessary because multicopters have much less control authority in yaw compared to the other axes and it makes sense because yaw is not critical for stable hovering or 3D navigation.  For yaw control tuning use MC_YAW_P. This ratio has no impact on the yaw gain.

MC_ROLLRATE_MAX.name: MC_ROLLRATE_MAX
MC_ROLLRATE_MAX.long_desc: Limit for roll rate in manual and auto modes (except acro). Has effect for large rotations in autonomous mode, to avoid large control output and mixer saturation.  This is not only limited by the vehicle's properties, but also by the maximum measurement rate of the gyro.

MC_PITCHRATE_MAX.name: MC_PITCHRATE_MAX
MC_PITCHRATE_MAX.long_desc: Limit for pitch rate in manual and auto modes (except acro). Has effect for large rotations in autonomous mode, to avoid large control output and mixer saturation.  This is not only limited by the vehicle's properties, but also by the maximum measurement rate of the gyro.

MC_MAN_TILT_TAU.name: MC_MAN_TILT_TAU
MC_MAN_TILT_TAU.short_desc: Manual tilt input filter time constant
MC_MAN_TILT_TAU.long_desc: Setting this parameter to 0 disables the filter

MC_AT_START.name: MC_AT_START
MC_AT_START.long_desc: WARNING: this will inject steps to the rate controller and can be dangerous. Only activate if you know what you are doing, and in a safe environment.  Any motion of the remote stick will abort the signal injection and reset this parameter Best is to perform the identification in position or hold mode. Increase the amplitude of the injected signal using MC_AT_SYSID_AMP for more signal/noise ratio

MC_AT_APPLY.name: MC_AT_APPLY
MC_AT_APPLY.short_desc: Controls when to apply the new gains
MC_AT_APPLY.long_desc: After the auto-tuning sequence is completed, a new set of gains is available and can be applied immediately or after landing.  WARNING Applying the gains in air is dangerous as there is no guarantee that those new gains will be able to stabilize the drone properly.

MC_AT_RISE_TIME.name: MC_AT_RISE_TIME
MC_AT_RISE_TIME.short_desc: Desired angular rate closed-loop rise time

HTE_HT_NOISE.name: HTE_HT_NOISE
HTE_HT_NOISE.long_desc: Reduce to make the hover thrust estimate more stable, increase if the real hover thrust is expected to change quickly over time.

HTE_ACC_GATE.name: HTE_ACC_GATE
HTE_ACC_GATE.long_desc: Sets the number of standard deviations used by the innovation consistency test.

HTE_HT_ERR_INIT.name: HTE_HT_ERR_INIT
HTE_HT_ERR_INIT.long_desc: Sets the number of standard deviations used by the innovation consistency test.

HTE_VXY_THR.name: HTE_VXY_THR
HTE_VXY_THR.short_desc: Horizontal velocity threshold for sensitivity reduction
HTE_VXY_THR.long_desc: Above this speed, the measurement noise is linearly increased to reduce the sensitivity of the estimator from biased measurement.  Set to a low value on vehicles with large lifting surfaces.

HTE_VZ_THR.name: HTE_VZ_THR
HTE_VZ_THR.short_desc: Vertical velocity threshold for sensitivity reduction
HTE_VZ_THR.long_desc: Above this speed, the measurement noise is linearly increased to reduce the sensitivity of the estimator from biased measurement.  Set to a low value on vehicles affected by air drag when climbing or descending.

HTE_THR_RANGE.name: HTE_THR_RANGE
HTE_THR_RANGE.long_desc: Defines the range of the hover thrust estimate around MPC_THR_HOVER. A value of 0.2 with MPC_THR_HOVER at 0.5 results in a range of [0.3, 0.7].  Set to a large value if the vehicle operates in varying physical conditions that affect the required hover thrust strongly (e.g. differently sized payloads).

MPC_ACC_UP_MAX.name: MPC_ACC_UP_MAX
MPC_ACC_UP_MAX.short_desc: Maximum upwards acceleration in climb rate controlled modes

MPC_ACC_DOWN_MAX.name: MPC_ACC_DOWN_MAX
MPC_ACC_DOWN_MAX.short_desc: Maximum downwards acceleration in climb rate controlled modes

MPC_MAN_Y_TAU.name: MPC_MAN_Y_TAU
MPC_MAN_Y_TAU.short_desc: Manual yaw rate input filter time constant
MPC_MAN_Y_TAU.long_desc: Not used in Stabilized mode Setting this parameter to 0 disables the filter

MPC_ALT_MODE.name: MPC_ALT_MODE
MPC_ALT_MODE.long_desc: Control height 0: relative earth frame origin which may drift due to sensors 1: relative to ground (requires distance sensor) which changes with terrain variation. It will revert to relative earth frame if the distance to ground estimate becomes invalid. 2: relative to ground (requires distance sensor) when stationary and relative to earth frame when moving horizontally. The speed threshold is MPC_HOLD_MAX_XY

MPC_HOLD_MAX_XY.name: MPC_HOLD_MAX_XY
MPC_HOLD_MAX_XY.short_desc: Maximum horizontal velocity for which position hold is enabled (use 0 to disable check)
MPC_HOLD_MAX_XY.long_desc: Only used with MPC_POS_MODE Direct velocity or MPC_ALT_MODE 2

MPC_HOLD_MAX_Z.name: MPC_HOLD_MAX_Z
MPC_HOLD_MAX_Z.short_desc: Maximum vertical velocity for which position hold is enabled (use 0 to disable check)

MPC_XY_CRUISE.name: MPC_XY_CRUISE
MPC_XY_CRUISE.short_desc: Default horizontal velocity in autonomous modes
MPC_XY_CRUISE.long_desc: e.g. in Missions, RTL, Goto if the waypoint does not specify differently

MPC_Z_V_AUTO_UP.name: MPC_Z_V_AUTO_UP
MPC_Z_V_AUTO_UP.long_desc: For manually controlled modes and offboard see MPC_Z_VEL_MAX_UP

MPC_Z_V_AUTO_DN.name: MPC_Z_V_AUTO_DN
MPC_Z_V_AUTO_DN.long_desc: For manual modes and offboard, see MPC_Z_VEL_MAX_DN

MPC_ACC_HOR.name: MPC_ACC_HOR
MPC_ACC_HOR.short_desc: Acceleration for autonomous and for manual modes
MPC_ACC_HOR.long_desc: When piloting manually, this parameter is only used in MPC_POS_MODE Acceleration based.

MPC_JERK_AUTO.name: MPC_JERK_AUTO
MPC_JERK_AUTO.long_desc: Limit the maximum jerk of the vehicle (how fast the acceleration can change). A lower value leads to smoother vehicle motions but also limited agility.

MPC_XY_TRAJ_P.name: MPC_XY_TRAJ_P
MPC_XY_TRAJ_P.short_desc: Proportional gain for horizontal trajectory position error

MPC_XY_ERR_MAX.name: MPC_XY_ERR_MAX
MPC_XY_ERR_MAX.short_desc: Maximum horizontal error allowed by the trajectory generator
MPC_XY_ERR_MAX.long_desc: The integration speed of the trajectory setpoint is linearly reduced with the horizontal position tracking error. When the error is above this parameter, the integration of the trajectory is stopped to wait for the drone.  This value can be adjusted depending on the tracking capabilities of the vehicle.

MPC_YAWRAUTO_MAX.name: MPC_YAWRAUTO_MAX
MPC_YAWRAUTO_MAX.short_desc: Maximum yaw rate in autonomous modes
MPC_YAWRAUTO_MAX.long_desc: Limits the rate of change of the yaw setpoint to avoid large control output and mixer saturation.

MPC_YAWRAUTO_ACC.name: MPC_YAWRAUTO_ACC
MPC_YAWRAUTO_ACC.short_desc: Maximum yaw acceleration in autonomous modes
MPC_YAWRAUTO_ACC.long_desc: Limits the acceleration of the yaw setpoint to avoid large control output and mixer saturation.

MPC_LAND_RC_HELP.name: MPC_LAND_RC_HELP
MPC_LAND_RC_HELP.short_desc: Enable nudging based on user input during autonomous land routine
MPC_LAND_RC_HELP.long_desc: Using stick input the vehicle can be moved horizontally and yawed. The descend speed is amended: stick full up - 0 stick centered - MPC_LAND_SPEED stick full down - 2 * MPC_LAND_SPEED  Manual override during auto modes has to be disabled to use this feature (see COM_RC_OVERRIDE).

MPC_LAND_RADIUS.name: MPC_LAND_RADIUS
MPC_LAND_RADIUS.long_desc: When nudging is enabled (see MPC_LAND_RC_HELP), this controls the maximum allowed horizontal displacement from the original landing point.

MPC_Z_P.name: MPC_Z_P
MPC_Z_P.short_desc: Proportional gain for vertical position error
MPC_Z_P.long_desc: Defined as corrective velocity in m/s per m position error

MPC_XY_P.name: MPC_XY_P
MPC_XY_P.short_desc: Proportional gain for horizontal position error
MPC_XY_P.long_desc: Defined as corrective velocity in m/s per m position error

MPC_Z_VEL_P_ACC.name: MPC_Z_VEL_P_ACC
MPC_Z_VEL_P_ACC.short_desc: Proportional gain for vertical velocity error
MPC_Z_VEL_P_ACC.long_desc: Defined as corrective acceleration in m/s^2 per m/s velocity error

MPC_XY_VEL_P_ACC.name: MPC_XY_VEL_P_ACC
MPC_XY_VEL_P_ACC.short_desc: Proportional gain for horizontal velocity error
MPC_XY_VEL_P_ACC.long_desc: Defined as corrective acceleration in m/s^2 per m/s velocity error

MPC_Z_VEL_I_ACC.name: MPC_Z_VEL_I_ACC
MPC_Z_VEL_I_ACC.short_desc: Integral gain for vertical velocity error
MPC_Z_VEL_I_ACC.long_desc: Defined as corrective acceleration in m/s^2 per m velocity integral

MPC_XY_VEL_I_ACC.name: MPC_XY_VEL_I_ACC
MPC_XY_VEL_I_ACC.short_desc: Integral gain for horizontal velocity error
MPC_XY_VEL_I_ACC.long_desc: Defined as correction acceleration in m/s^2 per m velocity integral Allows to eliminate steady state errors in disturbances like wind.

MPC_Z_VEL_D_ACC.name: MPC_Z_VEL_D_ACC
MPC_Z_VEL_D_ACC.short_desc: Differential gain for vertical velocity error
MPC_Z_VEL_D_ACC.long_desc: Defined as corrective acceleration in m/s^2 per m/s^2 velocity derivative

MPC_XY_VEL_D_ACC.name: MPC_XY_VEL_D_ACC
MPC_XY_VEL_D_ACC.short_desc: Differential gain for horizontal velocity error
MPC_XY_VEL_D_ACC.long_desc: Defined as corrective acceleration in m/s^2 per m/s^2 velocity derivative

MPC_XY_VEL_MAX.name: MPC_XY_VEL_MAX
MPC_XY_VEL_MAX.long_desc: Absolute maximum for all velocity controlled modes. Any higher value is truncated.

MPC_Z_VEL_MAX_UP.name: MPC_Z_VEL_MAX_UP
MPC_Z_VEL_MAX_UP.long_desc: Absolute maximum for all climb rate controlled modes. In manually piloted modes full stick deflection commands this velocity.  For default autonomous velocity see MPC_Z_V_AUTO_UP

MPC_Z_VEL_MAX_DN.name: MPC_Z_VEL_MAX_DN
MPC_Z_VEL_MAX_DN.long_desc: Absolute maximum for all climb rate controlled modes. In manually piloted modes full stick deflection commands this velocity.  For default autonomous velocity see MPC_Z_V_AUTO_UP

MPC_TILTMAX_AIR.name: MPC_TILTMAX_AIR
MPC_TILTMAX_AIR.long_desc: Absolute maximum for all velocity or acceleration controlled modes. Any higher value is truncated.

MPC_TILTMAX_LND.name: MPC_TILTMAX_LND
MPC_TILTMAX_LND.short_desc: Maximum tilt during inital takeoff ramp
MPC_TILTMAX_LND.long_desc: Tighter tilt limit during takeoff to avoid tip over.

MPC_THR_MIN.name: MPC_THR_MIN
MPC_THR_MIN.short_desc: Minimum collective thrust in climb rate controlled modes
MPC_THR_MIN.long_desc: Too low thrust leads to loss of roll/pitch/yaw torque control authority. With airmode enabled this parameters can be set to 0 while still keeping torque authority (see MC_AIRMODE).

MPC_THR_MAX.name: MPC_THR_MAX
MPC_THR_MAX.short_desc: Maximum collective thrust in climb rate controlled modes
MPC_THR_MAX.long_desc: Limit allowed thrust e.g. for indoor test of overpowered vehicle.

MPC_ACC_DECOUPLE.name: MPC_ACC_DECOUPLE
MPC_ACC_DECOUPLE.long_desc: Set to decouple tilt from vertical acceleration. This provides smoother flight but slightly worse tracking in position and auto modes. Unset if accurate position tracking during dynamic maneuvers is more important than a smooth flight.

MPC_THR_HOVER.name: MPC_THR_HOVER
MPC_THR_HOVER.long_desc: Mapped to center throttle stick in Stabilized mode (see MPC_THR_CURVE). Used for initialization of the hover thrust estimator (see MPC_USE_HTE). The estimated hover thrust is used as base for zero vertical acceleration in altitude control. The hover thrust is important for land detection to work correctly.

MPC_USE_HTE.name: MPC_USE_HTE
MPC_USE_HTE.long_desc: Disable to use the fixed parameter MPC_THR_HOVER Enable to use the hover thrust estimator

MPC_THR_XY_MARG.name: MPC_THR_XY_MARG
MPC_THR_XY_MARG.long_desc: Margin that is kept for horizontal control when higher priority vertical thrust is saturated. To avoid completely starving horizontal control with high vertical error.

MPC_VEL_LP.name: MPC_VEL_LP
MPC_VEL_LP.long_desc: A value of 0 disables the filter.

MPC_VEL_NF_FRQ.name: MPC_VEL_NF_FRQ
MPC_VEL_NF_FRQ.long_desc: The center frequency for the 2nd order notch filter on the velocity. A value of 0 disables the filter.

MPC_VEL_NF_BW.name: MPC_VEL_NF_BW
MPC_VEL_NF_BW.long_desc: A value of 0 disables the filter.

MPC_VELD_LP.name: MPC_VELD_LP
MPC_VELD_LP.short_desc: Velocity derivative low pass cutoff frequency
MPC_VELD_LP.long_desc: A value of 0 disables the filter.

MPC_POS_MODE.name: MPC_POS_MODE
MPC_POS_MODE.long_desc: The supported sub-modes are: Direct velocity: Sticks directly map to velocity setpoints without smoothing. Also applies to vertical direction and Altitude mode. Useful for velocity control tuning. Acceleration based: Sticks map to acceleration and there's a virtual brake drag

MPC_VEL_MANUAL.name: MPC_VEL_MANUAL
MPC_VEL_MANUAL.short_desc: Maximum horizontal velocity setpoint in Position mode
MPC_VEL_MANUAL.long_desc: Must be smaller than MPC_XY_VEL_MAX.  The maximum sideways and backward speed can be set differently using MPC_VEL_MAN_SIDE and MPC_VEL_MAN_BACK, respectively.

MPC_VEL_MAN_SIDE.name: MPC_VEL_MAN_SIDE
MPC_VEL_MAN_SIDE.short_desc: Maximum sideways velocity in Position mode
MPC_VEL_MAN_SIDE.long_desc: If set to a negative value or larger than MPC_VEL_MANUAL then MPC_VEL_MANUAL is used.

MPC_VEL_MAN_BACK.name: MPC_VEL_MAN_BACK
MPC_VEL_MAN_BACK.short_desc: Maximum backward velocity in Position mode
MPC_VEL_MAN_BACK.long_desc: If set to a negative value or larger than MPC_VEL_MANUAL then MPC_VEL_MANUAL is used.

MPC_ACC_HOR_MAX.name: MPC_ACC_HOR_MAX
MPC_ACC_HOR_MAX.long_desc: MPC_POS_MODE 1 just deceleration 4 not used, use MPC_ACC_HOR instead

MPC_JERK_MAX.name: MPC_JERK_MAX
MPC_JERK_MAX.short_desc: Maximum horizontal and vertical jerk in Position/Altitude mode
MPC_JERK_MAX.long_desc: Limit the maximum jerk (acceleration change) of the vehicle. A lower value leads to smoother motions but limits agility.  Setting this to the maximum value essentially disables the limit.  Only used with MPC_POS_MODE Acceleration based.

MPC_HOLD_DZ.name: MPC_HOLD_DZ
MPC_HOLD_DZ.short_desc: Deadzone for sticks in manual piloted modes
MPC_HOLD_DZ.long_desc: Does not apply to manual throttle and direct attitude piloting by stick.

MPC_XY_MAN_EXPO.name: MPC_XY_MAN_EXPO
MPC_XY_MAN_EXPO.short_desc: Manual position control stick exponential curve sensitivity
MPC_XY_MAN_EXPO.long_desc: The higher the value the less sensitivity the stick has around zero while still reaching the maximum value with full stick deflection.  0 Purely linear input curve 1 Purely cubic input curve

MPC_Z_MAN_EXPO.name: MPC_Z_MAN_EXPO
MPC_Z_MAN_EXPO.short_desc: Manual control stick vertical exponential curve
MPC_Z_MAN_EXPO.long_desc: The higher the value the less sensitivity the stick has around zero while still reaching the maximum value with full stick deflection.  0 Purely linear input curve 1 Purely cubic input curve

MPC_YAW_EXPO.name: MPC_YAW_EXPO
MPC_YAW_EXPO.short_desc: Manual control stick yaw rotation exponential curve
MPC_YAW_EXPO.long_desc: The higher the value the less sensitivity the stick has around zero while still reaching the maximum value with full stick deflection.  0 Purely linear input curve 1 Purely cubic input curve

SYS_VEHICLE_RESP.name: SYS_VEHICLE_RESP
SYS_VEHICLE_RESP.long_desc: Changes the overall responsiveness of the vehicle. The higher the value, the faster the vehicle will react.  If set to a value greater than zero, other parameters are automatically set (such as the acceleration or jerk limits). If set to a negative value, the existing individual parameters are used.

MPC_XY_VEL_ALL.name: MPC_XY_VEL_ALL
MPC_XY_VEL_ALL.long_desc: If set to a value greater than zero, other parameters are automatically set (such as MPC_XY_VEL_MAX or MPC_VEL_MANUAL). If set to a negative value, the existing individual parameters are used.

MPC_Z_VEL_ALL.name: MPC_Z_VEL_ALL
MPC_Z_VEL_ALL.long_desc: If set to a value greater than zero, other parameters are automatically set (such as MPC_Z_VEL_MAX_UP or MPC_LAND_SPEED). If set to a negative value, the existing individual parameters are used.

MPC_MAN_TILT_MAX.name: MPC_MAN_TILT_MAX
MPC_MAN_TILT_MAX.short_desc: Maximal tilt angle in Stabilized or Altitude mode

MPC_MAN_Y_MAX.name: MPC_MAN_Y_MAX
MPC_MAN_Y_MAX.short_desc: Max manual yaw rate for Stabilized, Altitude, Position mode

MPC_MANTHR_MIN.name: MPC_MANTHR_MIN
MPC_MANTHR_MIN.short_desc: Minimum collective thrust in Stabilized mode
MPC_MANTHR_MIN.long_desc: The value is mapped to the lowest throttle stick position in Stabilized mode.  Too low collective thrust leads to loss of roll/pitch/yaw torque control authority. Airmode is used to keep torque authority with zero thrust (see MC_AIRMODE).

MPC_THR_CURVE.name: MPC_THR_CURVE
MPC_THR_CURVE.short_desc: Thrust curve mapping in Stabilized Mode
MPC_THR_CURVE.long_desc: Defines how the throttle stick is mapped to collective thrust in Stabilized mode.  Rescale to hover thrust: Stick input is linearly rescaled, such that a centered stick corresponds to the hover throttle (see MPC_THR_HOVER).  No Rescale: Directly map the stick 1:1 to the output. Can be useful with very low hover thrust which leads to much distortion and the upper half getting sensitive.  With MPC_THR_HOVER 0.5 both modes are the same.

MPC_TKO_RAMP_T.name: MPC_TKO_RAMP_T
MPC_TKO_RAMP_T.long_desc: Increasing this value will make climb rate controlled takeoff slower. If it's too slow the drone might scratch the ground and tip over. A time constant of 0 disables the ramp

MPC_LAND_ALT1.name: MPC_LAND_ALT1
MPC_LAND_ALT1.short_desc: Altitude for 1. step of slow landing (descend)
MPC_LAND_ALT1.long_desc: Below this altitude descending velocity gets limited to a value between "MPC_Z_VEL_MAX_DN" (or "MPC_Z_V_AUTO_DN") and "MPC_LAND_SPEED" Value needs to be higher than "MPC_LAND_ALT2"

MPC_LAND_ALT2.name: MPC_LAND_ALT2
MPC_LAND_ALT2.short_desc: Altitude for 2. step of slow landing (landing)
MPC_LAND_ALT2.long_desc: Below this altitude descending velocity gets limited to "MPC_LAND_SPEED" Value needs to be lower than "MPC_LAND_ALT1"

MPC_LAND_ALT3.name: MPC_LAND_ALT3
MPC_LAND_ALT3.short_desc: Altitude for 3. step of slow landing
MPC_LAND_ALT3.long_desc: Below this altitude descending velocity gets limited to "MPC_LAND_CRWL", if LIDAR available. No effect if LIDAR not available

MPC_LAND_CRWL.name: MPC_LAND_CRWL
MPC_LAND_CRWL.long_desc: Used below MPC_LAND_ALT3 if distance sensor data is availabe.

MC_ACRO_R_MAX.name: MC_ACRO_R_MAX
MC_ACRO_R_MAX.long_desc: Full stick deflection leads to this rate.

MC_ACRO_P_MAX.name: MC_ACRO_P_MAX
MC_ACRO_P_MAX.long_desc: Full stick deflection leads to this rate.

MC_ACRO_Y_MAX.name: MC_ACRO_Y_MAX
MC_ACRO_Y_MAX.long_desc: Full stick deflection leads to this rate.

MC_ACRO_EXPO.name: MC_ACRO_EXPO
MC_ACRO_EXPO.short_desc: Acro mode roll, pitch expo factor
MC_ACRO_EXPO.long_desc: Exponential factor for tuning the input curve shape.  0 Purely linear input curve 1 Purely cubic input curve

MC_ACRO_EXPO_Y.name: MC_ACRO_EXPO_Y
MC_ACRO_EXPO_Y.long_desc: Exponential factor for tuning the input curve shape.  0 Purely linear input curve 1 Purely cubic input curve

MC_ACRO_SUPEXPO.name: MC_ACRO_SUPEXPO
MC_ACRO_SUPEXPO.short_desc: Acro mode roll, pitch super expo factor
MC_ACRO_SUPEXPO.long_desc: "Superexponential" factor for refining the input curve shape tuned using MC_ACRO_EXPO.  0 Pure Expo function 0.7 reasonable shape enhancement for intuitive stick feel 0.95 very strong bent input curve only near maxima have effect

MC_ACRO_SUPEXPOY.name: MC_ACRO_SUPEXPOY
MC_ACRO_SUPEXPOY.short_desc: Acro mode yaw super expo factor
MC_ACRO_SUPEXPOY.long_desc: "Superexponential" factor for refining the input curve shape tuned using MC_ACRO_EXPO_Y.  0 Pure Expo function 0.7 reasonable shape enhancement for intuitive stick feel 0.95 very strong bent input curve only near maxima have effect

MC_ROLLRATE_P.name: MC_ROLLRATE_P
MC_ROLLRATE_P.long_desc: Roll rate proportional gain, i.e. control output for angular speed error 1 rad/s.

MC_ROLLRATE_I.name: MC_ROLLRATE_I
MC_ROLLRATE_I.long_desc: Roll rate integral gain. Can be set to compensate static thrust difference or gravity center offset.

MC_RR_INT_LIM.name: MC_RR_INT_LIM
MC_RR_INT_LIM.long_desc: Roll rate integrator limit. Can be set to increase the amount of integrator available to counteract disturbances or reduced to improve settling time after large roll moment trim changes.

MC_ROLLRATE_D.name: MC_ROLLRATE_D
MC_ROLLRATE_D.long_desc: Roll rate differential gain. Small values help reduce fast oscillations. If value is too big oscillations will appear again.

MC_ROLLRATE_K.name: MC_ROLLRATE_K
MC_ROLLRATE_K.long_desc: Global gain of the controller.  This gain scales the P, I and D terms of the controller: output = MC_ROLLRATE_K * (MC_ROLLRATE_P * error 			     + MC_ROLLRATE_I * error_integral 			     + MC_ROLLRATE_D * error_derivative) Set MC_ROLLRATE_P=1 to implement a PID in the ideal form. Set MC_ROLLRATE_K=1 to implement a PID in the parallel form.

MC_PITCHRATE_P.name: MC_PITCHRATE_P
MC_PITCHRATE_P.long_desc: Pitch rate proportional gain, i.e. control output for angular speed error 1 rad/s.

MC_PITCHRATE_I.name: MC_PITCHRATE_I
MC_PITCHRATE_I.long_desc: Pitch rate integral gain. Can be set to compensate static thrust difference or gravity center offset.

MC_PR_INT_LIM.name: MC_PR_INT_LIM
MC_PR_INT_LIM.long_desc: Pitch rate integrator limit. Can be set to increase the amount of integrator available to counteract disturbances or reduced to improve settling time after large pitch moment trim changes.

MC_PITCHRATE_D.name: MC_PITCHRATE_D
MC_PITCHRATE_D.long_desc: Pitch rate differential gain. Small values help reduce fast oscillations. If value is too big oscillations will appear again.

MC_PITCHRATE_K.name: MC_PITCHRATE_K
MC_PITCHRATE_K.long_desc: Global gain of the controller.  This gain scales the P, I and D terms of the controller: output = MC_PITCHRATE_K * (MC_PITCHRATE_P * error 			     + MC_PITCHRATE_I * error_integral 			     + MC_PITCHRATE_D * error_derivative) Set MC_PITCHRATE_P=1 to implement a PID in the ideal form. Set MC_PITCHRATE_K=1 to implement a PID in the parallel form.

MC_YAWRATE_P.name: MC_YAWRATE_P
MC_YAWRATE_P.long_desc: Yaw rate proportional gain, i.e. control output for angular speed error 1 rad/s.

MC_YAWRATE_I.name: MC_YAWRATE_I
MC_YAWRATE_I.long_desc: Yaw rate integral gain. Can be set to compensate static thrust difference or gravity center offset.

MC_YR_INT_LIM.name: MC_YR_INT_LIM
MC_YR_INT_LIM.long_desc: Yaw rate integrator limit. Can be set to increase the amount of integrator available to counteract disturbances or reduced to improve settling time after large yaw moment trim changes.

MC_YAWRATE_D.name: MC_YAWRATE_D
MC_YAWRATE_D.long_desc: Yaw rate differential gain. Small values help reduce fast oscillations. If value is too big oscillations will appear again.

MC_YAWRATE_K.name: MC_YAWRATE_K
MC_YAWRATE_K.long_desc: Global gain of the controller.  This gain scales the P, I and D terms of the controller: output = MC_YAWRATE_K * (MC_YAWRATE_P * error 			     + MC_YAWRATE_I * error_integral 			     + MC_YAWRATE_D * error_derivative) Set MC_YAWRATE_P=1 to implement a PID in the ideal form. Set MC_YAWRATE_K=1 to implement a PID in the parallel form.

MC_BAT_SCALE_EN.name: MC_BAT_SCALE_EN
MC_BAT_SCALE_EN.long_desc: This compensates for voltage drop of the battery over time by attempting to normalize performance across the operating range of the battery. The copter should constantly behave as if it was fully charged with reduced max acceleration at lower battery percentages. i.e. if hover is at 0.5 throttle at 100% battery, it will still be 0.5 at 60% battery.

MC_YAW_TQ_CUTOFF.name: MC_YAW_TQ_CUTOFF
MC_YAW_TQ_CUTOFF.short_desc: Low pass filter cutoff frequency for yaw torque setpoint
MC_YAW_TQ_CUTOFF.long_desc: Reduces vibrations by lowering high frequency torque caused by rotor acceleration. 0 disables the filter

GF_ACTION.name: GF_ACTION
GF_ACTION.long_desc: Note: Setting this value to 4 enables flight termination, which will kill the vehicle on violation of the fence.

GF_SOURCE.name: GF_SOURCE
GF_SOURCE.long_desc: Select which position source should be used. Selecting GPS instead of global position makes sure that there is no dependence on the position estimator 0 = global position, 1 = GPS

GF_MAX_HOR_DIST.name: GF_MAX_HOR_DIST
GF_MAX_HOR_DIST.long_desc: Maximum horizontal distance in meters the vehicle can be from Home before triggering a geofence action. Disabled if 0.

GF_MAX_VER_DIST.name: GF_MAX_VER_DIST
GF_MAX_VER_DIST.long_desc: Maximum vertical distance in meters the vehicle can be from Home before triggering a geofence action. Disabled if 0.

GF_PREDICT.name: GF_PREDICT
GF_PREDICT.long_desc: WARNING: This experimental feature may cause flyaways. Use at your own risk.  Predict the motion of the vehicle and trigger the breach if it is determined that the current trajectory would result in a breach happening before the vehicle can make evasive maneuvers. The vehicle is then re-routed to a safe hold position (stop for multirotor, loiter for fixed wing).

MIS_TAKEOFF_ALT.name: MIS_TAKEOFF_ALT
MIS_TAKEOFF_ALT.long_desc: This is the relative altitude the system will take off to if not otherwise specified.

MIS_TKO_LAND_REQ.name: MIS_TKO_LAND_REQ
MIS_TKO_LAND_REQ.long_desc: Specifies if a mission has to contain a takeoff and/or mission landing. Validity of configured takeoffs/landings is checked independently of the setting here.

MIS_DIST_1WP.name: MIS_DIST_1WP
MIS_DIST_1WP.short_desc: Maximal horizontal distance from Home to first waypoint
MIS_DIST_1WP.long_desc: There will be a warning message if the current waypoint is more distant than MIS_DIST_1WP from Home. Has no effect on mission validity. Set a value of zero or less to disable.

MIS_MNT_YAW_CTL.name: MIS_MNT_YAW_CTL
MIS_MNT_YAW_CTL.short_desc: Enable yaw control of the mount. (Only affects multicopters and ROI mission items)
MIS_MNT_YAW_CTL.long_desc: If enabled, yaw commands will be sent to the mount and the vehicle will follow its heading towards the flight direction. If disabled, the vehicle will yaw towards the ROI.

MIS_YAW_TMT.name: MIS_YAW_TMT
MIS_YAW_TMT.short_desc: Time in seconds we wait on reaching target heading at a waypoint if it is forced.
MIS_YAW_TMT.long_desc: If set > 0 it will ignore the target heading for normal waypoint acceptance. If the waypoint forces the heading the timeout will matter. For example on VTOL forwards transition. Mainly useful for VTOLs that have less yaw authority and might not reach target yaw in wind. Disabled by default.

MIS_YAW_ERR.name: MIS_YAW_ERR
MIS_YAW_ERR.short_desc: Max yaw error in degrees needed for waypoint heading acceptance.

MIS_LND_ABRT_ALT.name: MIS_LND_ABRT_ALT
MIS_LND_ABRT_ALT.long_desc: Minimum altitude above landing point that the vehicle will climb to after an aborted landing. Then vehicle will loiter in this altitude until further command is received. Only applies to fixed-wing vehicles.

MIS_COMMAND_TOUT.name: MIS_COMMAND_TOUT
MIS_COMMAND_TOUT.short_desc: Timeout to allow the payload to execute the mission command
MIS_COMMAND_TOUT.long_desc: Ensure: gripper: NAV_CMD_DO_GRIPPER has released before continuing mission. winch: CMD_DO_WINCH has delivered before continuing mission. gimbal: CMD_DO_GIMBAL_MANAGER_PITCHYAW has reached the commanded orientation before beginning to take pictures.

NAV_LOITER_RAD.name: NAV_LOITER_RAD
NAV_LOITER_RAD.long_desc: Default value of loiter radius in FW mode (e.g. for Loiter mode).

NAV_ACC_RAD.name: NAV_ACC_RAD
NAV_ACC_RAD.long_desc: Default acceptance radius, overridden by acceptance radius of waypoint if set. For fixed wing the npfg switch distance is used for horizontal acceptance.

NAV_FW_ALTL_RAD.name: NAV_FW_ALTL_RAD
NAV_FW_ALTL_RAD.short_desc: FW Altitude Acceptance Radius before a landing
NAV_FW_ALTL_RAD.long_desc: Altitude acceptance used for the last waypoint before a fixed-wing landing. This is usually smaller than the standard vertical acceptance because close to the ground higher accuracy is required.

NAV_TRAFF_AVOID.name: NAV_TRAFF_AVOID
NAV_TRAFF_AVOID.long_desc: Enabling this will allow the system to respond to transponder data from e.g. ADSB transponders

NAV_TRAFF_A_HOR.name: NAV_TRAFF_A_HOR
NAV_TRAFF_A_HOR.short_desc: Set NAV TRAFFIC AVOID horizontal distance

NAV_TRAFF_A_VER.name: NAV_TRAFF_A_VER
NAV_TRAFF_A_VER.short_desc: Set NAV TRAFFIC AVOID vertical distance

NAV_TRAFF_COLL_T.name: NAV_TRAFF_COLL_T
NAV_TRAFF_COLL_T.long_desc: Minimum acceptable time until collsion. Assumes constant speed over 3d distance.

NAV_FORCE_VT.name: NAV_FORCE_VT
NAV_FORCE_VT.short_desc: Force VTOL mode takeoff and land

NAV_MIN_LTR_ALT.name: NAV_MIN_LTR_ALT
NAV_MIN_LTR_ALT.long_desc: This is the minimum altitude above Home the system will always obey in Loiter (Hold) mode if switched into this mode without specifying an altitude (e.g. through Loiter switch on RC). Doesn't affect Loiters that are part of Missions or that are entered through a reposition setpoint ("Go to"). Set to a negative value to disable.

NAV_MIN_GND_DIST.name: NAV_MIN_GND_DIST
NAV_MIN_GND_DIST.short_desc: Minimum height above ground during Mission and RTL
NAV_MIN_GND_DIST.long_desc: Minimum height above ground the vehicle is allowed to descend to during Mission and RTL, excluding landing commands. Requires a distance sensor to be set up. Note: only prevents the vehicle from descending further, but does not force it to climb.  Set to a negative value to disable.

PLD_BTOUT.name: PLD_BTOUT
PLD_BTOUT.long_desc: Time after which the landing target is considered lost without any new measurements.

PLD_HACC_RAD.name: PLD_HACC_RAD
PLD_HACC_RAD.long_desc: Start descending if closer above landing target than this.

PLD_FAPPR_ALT.name: PLD_FAPPR_ALT
PLD_FAPPR_ALT.long_desc: Allow final approach (without horizontal positioning) if losing landing target closer than this to the ground.

PLD_SRCH_ALT.name: PLD_SRCH_ALT
PLD_SRCH_ALT.long_desc: Altitude above home to which to climb when searching for the landing target.

PLD_SRCH_TOUT.name: PLD_SRCH_TOUT
PLD_SRCH_TOUT.long_desc: Time allowed to search for the landing target before falling back to normal landing.

PLD_MAX_SRCH.name: PLD_MAX_SRCH
PLD_MAX_SRCH.long_desc: Maximum number of times to search for the landing target if it is lost during the precision landing.

RTL_RETURN_ALT.name: RTL_RETURN_ALT
RTL_RETURN_ALT.long_desc: Default minimum altitude above destination (e.g. home, safe point, landing pattern) for return flight. The vehicle will climb to this altitude when Return mode is enganged, unless it currently is flying higher already. This is affected by RTL_MIN_DIST and RTL_CONE_ANG.

RTL_DESCEND_ALT.name: RTL_DESCEND_ALT
RTL_DESCEND_ALT.long_desc: Descend to this altitude (above destination position) after return, and wait for time defined in RTL_LAND_DELAY. Land (i.e. slowly descend) from this altitude if autolanding allowed. VTOLs do transition to hover in this altitdue above the landing point.

RTL_LAND_DELAY.name: RTL_LAND_DELAY
RTL_LAND_DELAY.long_desc: Delay before landing (after initial descent) in Return mode. If set to -1 the system will not land but loiter at RTL_DESCEND_ALT.

RTL_MIN_DIST.name: RTL_MIN_DIST
RTL_MIN_DIST.short_desc: Horizontal radius from return point within which special rules for return mode apply.
RTL_MIN_DIST.long_desc: The return altitude will be calculated based on RTL_CONE_ANG parameter. The yaw setpoint will switch to the one defined by corresponding waypoint.

RTL_TYPE.name: RTL_TYPE
RTL_TYPE.long_desc: Return mode destination and flight path (home location, rally point, mission landing pattern, reverse mission)

RTL_CONE_ANG.name: RTL_CONE_ANG
RTL_CONE_ANG.short_desc: Half-angle of the return mode altitude cone
RTL_CONE_ANG.long_desc: Defines the half-angle of a cone centered around the destination position that affects the altitude at which the vehicle returns.

RTL_PLD_MD.name: RTL_PLD_MD
RTL_PLD_MD.long_desc: Use precision landing when doing an RTL landing phase. This setting does not apply for RTL destinations planned as part of a mission.

RTL_LOITER_RAD.name: RTL_LOITER_RAD
RTL_LOITER_RAD.long_desc: Set the radius for loitering to a safe altitude for VTOL transition.

RTL_TIME_FACTOR.name: RTL_TIME_FACTOR
RTL_TIME_FACTOR.short_desc: RTL time estimate safety margin factor
RTL_TIME_FACTOR.long_desc: Safety factor that is used to scale the actual RTL time estimate. Time with margin = RTL_TIME_FACTOR * time + RTL_TIME_MARGIN

RTL_TIME_MARGIN.name: RTL_TIME_MARGIN
RTL_TIME_MARGIN.short_desc: RTL time estimate safety margin offset
RTL_TIME_MARGIN.long_desc: Margin that is added to the time estimate, after it has already been scaled Time with margin = RTL_TIME_FACTOR * time + RTL_TIME_MARGIN

RTL_APPR_FORCE.name: RTL_APPR_FORCE
RTL_APPR_FORCE.long_desc: Only consider RTL point, if it has an approach defined.

VTO_LOITER_ALT.name: VTO_LOITER_ALT
VTO_LOITER_ALT.long_desc: Altitude relative to home at which vehicle will loiter after front transition.

RC1_DZ.name: RC1_DZ
RC1_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC2_DZ.name: RC2_DZ
RC2_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC3_DZ.name: RC3_DZ
RC3_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC4_DZ.name: RC4_DZ
RC4_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC5_DZ.name: RC5_DZ
RC5_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC6_DZ.name: RC6_DZ
RC6_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC7_DZ.name: RC7_DZ
RC7_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC8_DZ.name: RC8_DZ
RC8_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC9_DZ.name: RC9_DZ
RC9_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC10_DZ.name: RC10_DZ
RC10_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC11_DZ.name: RC11_DZ
RC11_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC12_DZ.name: RC12_DZ
RC12_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC13_DZ.name: RC13_DZ
RC13_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC14_DZ.name: RC14_DZ
RC14_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC15_DZ.name: RC15_DZ
RC15_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC16_DZ.name: RC16_DZ
RC16_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC17_DZ.name: RC17_DZ
RC17_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC18_DZ.name: RC18_DZ
RC18_DZ.long_desc: The +- range of this value around the trim value will be considered as zero.

RC_CHAN_CNT.name: RC_CHAN_CNT
RC_CHAN_CNT.long_desc: This parameter is used by Ground Station software to save the number of channels which were used during RC calibration. It is only meant for ground station use.

RC_MAP_ROLL.name: RC_MAP_ROLL
RC_MAP_ROLL.long_desc: The channel index (starting from 1 for channel 1) indicates which channel should be used for reading roll inputs from. A value of zero indicates the switch is not assigned.

RC_MAP_PITCH.name: RC_MAP_PITCH
RC_MAP_PITCH.long_desc: The channel index (starting from 1 for channel 1) indicates which channel should be used for reading pitch inputs from. A value of zero indicates the switch is not assigned.

RC_MAP_FAILSAFE.name: RC_MAP_FAILSAFE
RC_MAP_FAILSAFE.long_desc: Configures which RC channel is used by the receiver to indicate the signal was lost (on receivers that use output a fixed signal value to report lost signal). If set to 0, the channel mapped to throttle is used.  Use RC_FAILS_THR to set the threshold indicating lost signal. By default it's below the expected range and hence disabled.

RC_MAP_THROTTLE.name: RC_MAP_THROTTLE
RC_MAP_THROTTLE.long_desc: The channel index (starting from 1 for channel 1) indicates which channel should be used for reading throttle inputs from. A value of zero indicates the switch is not assigned.

RC_MAP_YAW.name: RC_MAP_YAW
RC_MAP_YAW.long_desc: The channel index (starting from 1 for channel 1) indicates which channel should be used for reading yaw inputs from. A value of zero indicates the switch is not assigned.

RC_MAP_FLTMODE.name: RC_MAP_FLTMODE
RC_MAP_FLTMODE.long_desc: If this parameter is non-zero, flight modes are only selected by this channel and are assigned to six slots.

RC_MAP_ARM_SW.name: RC_MAP_ARM_SW
RC_MAP_ARM_SW.long_desc: Use it to arm/disarm via switch instead of default throttle stick. If this is assigned, arming and disarming via stick is disabled.

RC_MAP_FLTM_BTN.name: RC_MAP_FLTM_BTN
RC_MAP_FLTM_BTN.long_desc: This bitmask allows to specify multiple channels for changing flight modes using momentary buttons. Each channel is assigned to a mode slot ((lowest channel = slot 1). The resulting modes for each slot X is defined by the COM_FLTMODEX parameters. The functionality can be used only if RC_MAP_FLTMODE is disabled.  The maximum number of available slots and hence bits set in the mask is 6.

RC_MAP_PARAM1.name: RC_MAP_PARAM1
RC_MAP_PARAM1.long_desc: Can be used for parameter tuning with the RC. This one is further referenced as the 1st parameter channel. Set to 0 to deactivate

RC_MAP_PARAM2.name: RC_MAP_PARAM2
RC_MAP_PARAM2.long_desc: Can be used for parameter tuning with the RC. This one is further referenced as the 2nd parameter channel. Set to 0 to deactivate

RC_MAP_PARAM3.name: RC_MAP_PARAM3
RC_MAP_PARAM3.long_desc: Can be used for parameter tuning with the RC. This one is further referenced as the 3th parameter channel. Set to 0 to deactivate

RC_MAP_ENG_MOT.name: RC_MAP_ENG_MOT
RC_MAP_ENG_MOT.short_desc: RC channel to engage the main motor (for helicopters)

RC_FAILS_THR.name: RC_FAILS_THR
RC_FAILS_THR.long_desc: Use RC_MAP_FAILSAFE to specify which channel is used to indicate RC loss via this threshold. By default this is the throttle channel.  Set to a PWM value slightly above the PWM value for the channel (e.g. throttle) in a failsafe event, but below the minimum PWM value for the channel during normal operation.  Note: The default value of 0 disables the feature (it is below the expected range).

RC_RETURN_TH.name: RC_RETURN_TH
RC_RETURN_TH.short_desc: Threshold for selecting return to launch mode
RC_RETURN_TH.long_desc: 0-1 indicate where in the full channel range the threshold sits 		0 : min 		1 : max sign indicates polarity of comparison 		positive : true when channel>th 		negative : true when channel<th

RC_LOITER_TH.name: RC_LOITER_TH
RC_LOITER_TH.long_desc: 0-1 indicate where in the full channel range the threshold sits 		0 : min 		1 : max sign indicates polarity of comparison 		positive : true when channel>th 		negative : true when channel<th

RC_OFFB_TH.name: RC_OFFB_TH
RC_OFFB_TH.long_desc: 0-1 indicate where in the full channel range the threshold sits 		0 : min 		1 : max sign indicates polarity of comparison 		positive : true when channel>th 		negative : true when channel<th

RC_KILLSWITCH_TH.name: RC_KILLSWITCH_TH
RC_KILLSWITCH_TH.long_desc: 0-1 indicate where in the full channel range the threshold sits 		0 : min 		1 : max sign indicates polarity of comparison 		positive : true when channel>th 		negative : true when channel<th

RC_ARMSWITCH_TH.name: RC_ARMSWITCH_TH
RC_ARMSWITCH_TH.long_desc: 0-1 indicate where in the full channel range the threshold sits 		0 : min 		1 : max sign indicates polarity of comparison 		positive : true when channel>th 		negative : true when channel<th

RC_TRANS_TH.name: RC_TRANS_TH
RC_TRANS_TH.short_desc: Threshold for the VTOL transition switch
RC_TRANS_TH.long_desc: 0-1 indicate where in the full channel range the threshold sits 		0 : min 		1 : max sign indicates polarity of comparison 		positive : true when channel>th 		negative : true when channel<th

RC_GEAR_TH.name: RC_GEAR_TH
RC_GEAR_TH.short_desc: Threshold for the landing gear switch
RC_GEAR_TH.long_desc: 0-1 indicate where in the full channel range the threshold sits 		0 : min 		1 : max sign indicates polarity of comparison 		positive : true when channel>th 		negative : true when channel<th

RC_ENG_MOT_TH.name: RC_ENG_MOT_TH
RC_ENG_MOT_TH.short_desc: Threshold for selecting main motor engage
RC_ENG_MOT_TH.long_desc: 0-1 indicate where in the full channel range the threshold sits 		0 : min 		1 : max sign indicates polarity of comparison 		positive : true when channel>th 		negative : true when channel<th

RC_PAYLOAD_TH.name: RC_PAYLOAD_TH
RC_PAYLOAD_TH.short_desc: Threshold for selecting payload power switch
RC_PAYLOAD_TH.long_desc: 0-1 indicate where in the full channel range the threshold sits 		0 : min 		1 : max sign indicates polarity of comparison 		positive : true when channel>th 		negative : true when channel<th

RC_RSSI_PWM_CHAN.name: RC_RSSI_PWM_CHAN
RC_RSSI_PWM_CHAN.short_desc: PWM input channel that provides RSSI.
RC_RSSI_PWM_CHAN.long_desc: 0: do not read RSSI from input channel 1-18: read RSSI from specified input channel  Specify the range for RSSI input with RC_RSSI_PWM_MIN and RC_RSSI_PWM_MAX parameters.

RC_RSSI_PWM_MIN.name: RC_RSSI_PWM_MIN
RC_RSSI_PWM_MIN.short_desc: Min input value for RSSI reading.

RC_RSSI_PWM_MAX.name: RC_RSSI_PWM_MAX
RC_RSSI_PWM_MAX.short_desc: Max input value for RSSI reading.

RC_MAP_MODE_SW.name: RC_MAP_MODE_SW
RC_MAP_MODE_SW.long_desc: This is the main flight mode selector. The channel index (starting from 1 for channel 1) indicates which channel should be used for deciding about the main mode. A value of zero indicates the switch is not assigned.

GND_WHEEL_BASE.name: GND_WHEEL_BASE
GND_WHEEL_BASE.short_desc: Distance from front axle to rear axle
GND_WHEEL_BASE.long_desc: A value of 0.31 is typical for 1/10 RC cars.

GND_L1_DIST.name: GND_L1_DIST
GND_L1_DIST.long_desc: This is the distance at which the next waypoint is activated. This should be set to about 2-4x of GND_WHEEL_BASE and not smaller than one meter (due to GPS accuracy).

GND_L1_PERIOD.name: GND_L1_PERIOD
GND_L1_PERIOD.long_desc: This is the L1 distance and defines the tracking point ahead of the rover it's following. Use values around 2-5m for a 0.3m wheel base. Tuning instructions: Shorten slowly during tuning until response is sharp without oscillation.

GND_THR_CRUISE.name: GND_THR_CRUISE
GND_THR_CRUISE.long_desc: This is the throttle setting required to achieve the desired cruise speed. 10% is ok for a traxxas stampede vxl with ESC set to training mode

GND_THR_MAX.name: GND_THR_MAX
GND_THR_MAX.long_desc: This is the maximum throttle % that can be used by the controller. For a Traxxas stampede vxl with the ESC set to training, 30 % is enough

GND_THR_MIN.name: GND_THR_MIN
GND_THR_MIN.long_desc: This is the minimum throttle % that can be used by the controller. Set to 0 for rover

GND_SP_CTRL_MODE.name: GND_SP_CTRL_MODE
GND_SP_CTRL_MODE.long_desc: This allows the user to choose between closed loop gps speed or open loop cruise throttle speed

GND_SPEED_P.name: GND_SPEED_P
GND_SPEED_P.long_desc: This is the proportional gain for the speed closed loop controller

GND_SPEED_I.name: GND_SPEED_I
GND_SPEED_I.long_desc: This is the integral gain for the speed closed loop controller

GND_SPEED_D.name: GND_SPEED_D
GND_SPEED_D.long_desc: This is the derivative gain for the speed closed loop controller

GND_SPEED_IMAX.name: GND_SPEED_IMAX
GND_SPEED_IMAX.long_desc: This is the maxim value the integral can reach to prevent wind-up.

GND_SPEED_THR_SC.name: GND_SPEED_THR_SC
GND_SPEED_THR_SC.long_desc: This is a gain to map the speed control output to the throttle linearly.

GND_MAX_ANG.name: GND_MAX_ANG
GND_MAX_ANG.short_desc: Maximum turn angle for Ackerman steering.
GND_MAX_ANG.long_desc: At a control output of 0, the steering wheels are at 0 radians. At a control output of 1, the steering wheels are at GND_MAX_ANG radians.

CAL_AIR_CMODEL.name: CAL_AIR_CMODEL
CAL_AIR_CMODEL.short_desc: Airspeed sensor compensation model for the SDP3x
CAL_AIR_CMODEL.long_desc: Model with Pitot 		CAL_AIR_TUBED_MM: Not used, 1.5 mm tubes assumed. 		CAL_AIR_TUBELEN: Length of the tubes connecting the pitot to the sensor. Model without Pitot (1.5 mm tubes) 		CAL_AIR_TUBED_MM: Not used, 1.5 mm tubes assumed. 		CAL_AIR_TUBELEN: Length of the tubes connecting the pitot to the sensor. Tube Pressure Drop 		CAL_AIR_TUBED_MM: Diameter in mm of the pitot and tubes, must have the same diameter. 		CAL_AIR_TUBELEN: Length of the tubes connecting the pitot to the sensor and the static + dynamic port length of the pitot.

CAL_AIR_TUBELEN.name: CAL_AIR_TUBELEN
CAL_AIR_TUBELEN.long_desc: See the CAL_AIR_CMODEL explanation on how this parameter should be set.

CAL_AIR_TUBED_MM.name: CAL_AIR_TUBED_MM
CAL_AIR_TUBED_MM.short_desc: Airspeed sensor tube diameter. Only used for the Tube Pressure Drop Compensation.

SENS_DPRES_ANSC.name: SENS_DPRES_ANSC
SENS_DPRES_ANSC.long_desc: Pick the appropriate scaling from the datasheet. this number defines the (linear) conversion from voltage to Pascal (pa). For the MPXV7002DP this is 1000.  NOTE: If the sensor always registers zero, try switching the static and dynamic tubes.

SENS_BOARD_ROT.name: SENS_BOARD_ROT
SENS_BOARD_ROT.long_desc: This parameter defines the rotation of the FMU board relative to the platform.

SENS_BOARD_Y_OFF.name: SENS_BOARD_Y_OFF
SENS_BOARD_Y_OFF.long_desc: This parameter defines a rotational offset in degrees around the Y (Pitch) axis. It allows the user to fine tune the board offset in the event of misalignment.

SENS_BOARD_X_OFF.name: SENS_BOARD_X_OFF
SENS_BOARD_X_OFF.long_desc: This parameter defines a rotational offset in degrees around the X (Roll) axis It allows the user to fine tune the board offset in the event of misalignment.

SENS_BOARD_Z_OFF.name: SENS_BOARD_Z_OFF
SENS_BOARD_Z_OFF.long_desc: This parameter defines a rotational offset in degrees around the Z (Yaw) axis. It allows the user to fine tune the board offset in the event of misalignment.

SENS_EXT_I2C_PRB.name: SENS_EXT_I2C_PRB
SENS_EXT_I2C_PRB.long_desc: Probe for optional external I2C devices.

SENS_INT_BARO_EN.name: SENS_INT_BARO_EN
SENS_INT_BARO_EN.long_desc: For systems with an external barometer, this should be set to false to make sure that the external is used.

SENS_FLOW_ROT.name: SENS_FLOW_ROT
SENS_FLOW_ROT.long_desc: This parameter defines the yaw rotation of the optical flow relative to the vehicle body frame. Zero rotation is defined as X on flow board pointing towards front of vehicle.

SENS_FLOW_MINHGT.name: SENS_FLOW_MINHGT
SENS_FLOW_MINHGT.short_desc: Minimum height above ground when reliant on optical flow.
SENS_FLOW_MINHGT.long_desc: This parameter defines the minimum distance from ground at which the optical flow sensor operates reliably. The sensor may be usable below this height, but accuracy will progressively reduce to loss of focus.

SENS_FLOW_MAXHGT.name: SENS_FLOW_MAXHGT
SENS_FLOW_MAXHGT.short_desc: Maximum height above ground when reliant on optical flow.
SENS_FLOW_MAXHGT.long_desc: This parameter defines the maximum distance from ground at which the optical flow sensor operates reliably. The height setpoint will be limited to be no greater than this value when the navigation system is completely reliant on optical flow data and the height above ground estimate is valid. The sensor may be usable above this height, but accuracy will progressively degrade.

SENS_FLOW_MAXR.name: SENS_FLOW_MAXR
SENS_FLOW_MAXR.short_desc: Magnitude of maximum angular flow rate reliably measurable by the optical flow sensor.
SENS_FLOW_MAXR.long_desc: Optical flow data will not fused by the estimators if the magnitude of the flow rate exceeds this value and control loops will be instructed to limit ground speed such that the flow rate produced by movement over ground is less than 50% of this value.

SENS_FLOW_RATE.name: SENS_FLOW_RATE
SENS_FLOW_RATE.long_desc: Optical flow data maximum publication rate. This is an upper bound, actual optical flow data rate is still dependent on the sensor.

SENS_MAG_SIDES.name: SENS_MAG_SIDES
SENS_MAG_SIDES.short_desc: Bitfield selecting mag sides for calibration
SENS_MAG_SIDES.long_desc: If set to two side calibration, only the offsets are estimated, the scale calibration is left unchanged. Thus an initial six side calibration is recommended.  Bits: ORIENTATION_TAIL_DOWN = 1 ORIENTATION_NOSE_DOWN = 2 ORIENTATION_LEFT = 4 ORIENTATION_RIGHT = 8 ORIENTATION_UPSIDE_DOWN = 16 ORIENTATION_RIGHTSIDE_UP = 32

SENS_MAG_AUTOROT.name: SENS_MAG_AUTOROT
SENS_MAG_AUTOROT.long_desc: During calibration attempt to automatically determine the rotation of external magnetometers.

SENS_MAG_RATE.name: SENS_MAG_RATE
SENS_MAG_RATE.long_desc: Magnetometer data maximum publication rate. This is an upper bound, actual magnetometer data rate is still dependent on the sensor.

SENS_MAG_AUTOCAL.name: SENS_MAG_AUTOCAL
SENS_MAG_AUTOCAL.long_desc: Automatically initialize magnetometer calibration from bias estimate if available.

IMU_ACCEL_CUTOFF.name: IMU_ACCEL_CUTOFF
IMU_ACCEL_CUTOFF.short_desc: Low pass filter cutoff frequency for accel
IMU_ACCEL_CUTOFF.long_desc: The cutoff frequency for the 2nd order butterworth filter on the primary accelerometer. This only affects the signal sent to the controllers, not the estimators. 0 disables the filter.

SENS_BARO_RATE.name: SENS_BARO_RATE
SENS_BARO_RATE.long_desc: Barometric air data maximum publication rate. This is an upper bound, actual barometric data rate is still dependent on the sensor.

IMU_GYRO_NF0_FRQ.name: IMU_GYRO_NF0_FRQ
IMU_GYRO_NF0_FRQ.long_desc: The center frequency for the 2nd order notch filter on the primary gyro. This filter can be enabled to avoid feedback amplification of structural resonances at a specific frequency. This only affects the signal sent to the controllers, not the estimators. Applies to both angular velocity and angular acceleration sent to the controllers. See "IMU_GYRO_NF0_BW" to set the bandwidth of the filter.  A value of 0 disables the filter.

IMU_GYRO_NF0_BW.name: IMU_GYRO_NF0_BW
IMU_GYRO_NF0_BW.long_desc: The frequency width of the stop band for the 2nd order notch filter on the primary gyro. See "IMU_GYRO_NF0_FRQ" to activate the filter and to set the notch frequency. Applies to both angular velocity and angular acceleration sent to the controllers.

IMU_GYRO_NF1_FRQ.name: IMU_GYRO_NF1_FRQ
IMU_GYRO_NF1_FRQ.long_desc: The center frequency for the 2nd order notch filter on the primary gyro. This filter can be enabled to avoid feedback amplification of structural resonances at a specific frequency. This only affects the signal sent to the controllers, not the estimators. Applies to both angular velocity and angular acceleration sent to the controllers. See "IMU_GYRO_NF1_BW" to set the bandwidth of the filter.  A value of 0 disables the filter.

IMU_GYRO_NF1_BW.name: IMU_GYRO_NF1_BW
IMU_GYRO_NF1_BW.long_desc: The frequency width of the stop band for the 2nd order notch filter on the primary gyro. See "IMU_GYRO_NF1_FRQ" to activate the filter and to set the notch frequency. Applies to both angular velocity and angular acceleration sent to the controllers.

IMU_GYRO_CUTOFF.name: IMU_GYRO_CUTOFF
IMU_GYRO_CUTOFF.short_desc: Low pass filter cutoff frequency for gyro
IMU_GYRO_CUTOFF.long_desc: The cutoff frequency for the 2nd order butterworth filter on the primary gyro. This only affects the angular velocity sent to the controllers, not the estimators. It applies also to the angular acceleration (D-Term filter), see IMU_DGYRO_CUTOFF.  A value of 0 disables the filter.

IMU_GYRO_RATEMAX.name: IMU_GYRO_RATEMAX
IMU_GYRO_RATEMAX.short_desc: Gyro control data maximum publication rate (inner loop rate)
IMU_GYRO_RATEMAX.long_desc: The maximum rate the gyro control data (vehicle_angular_velocity) will be allowed to publish at. This is the loop rate for the rate controller and outputs.  Note: sensor data is always read and filtered at the full raw rate (eg commonly 8 kHz) regardless of this setting.

IMU_DGYRO_CUTOFF.name: IMU_DGYRO_CUTOFF
IMU_DGYRO_CUTOFF.short_desc: Cutoff frequency for angular acceleration (D-Term filter)
IMU_DGYRO_CUTOFF.long_desc: The cutoff frequency for the 2nd order butterworth filter used on the time derivative of the measured angular velocity, also known as the D-term filter in the rate controller. The D-term uses the derivative of the rate and thus is the most susceptible to noise. Therefore, using a D-term filter allows to increase IMU_GYRO_CUTOFF, which leads to reduced control latency and permits to increase the P gains.  A value of 0 disables the filter.

IMU_GYRO_DNF_EN.name: IMU_GYRO_DNF_EN
IMU_GYRO_DNF_EN.long_desc: Enable bank of dynamically updating notch filters. Requires ESC RPM feedback or onboard FFT (IMU_GYRO_FFT_EN).

IMU_GYRO_DNF_BW.name: IMU_GYRO_DNF_BW
IMU_GYRO_DNF_BW.short_desc: IMU gyro ESC notch filter bandwidth
IMU_GYRO_DNF_BW.long_desc: Bandwidth per notch filter when using dynamic notch filtering with ESC RPM.

IMU_GYRO_DNF_HMC.name: IMU_GYRO_DNF_HMC
IMU_GYRO_DNF_HMC.short_desc: IMU gyro dynamic notch filter harmonics
IMU_GYRO_DNF_HMC.long_desc: ESC RPM number of harmonics (multiples of RPM) for ESC RPM dynamic notch filtering.

IMU_GYRO_DNF_MIN.name: IMU_GYRO_DNF_MIN
IMU_GYRO_DNF_MIN.short_desc: IMU gyro dynamic notch filter minimum frequency
IMU_GYRO_DNF_MIN.long_desc: Minimum notch filter frequency in Hz.

SENS_GPS_MASK.name: SENS_GPS_MASK
SENS_GPS_MASK.long_desc: Set bits in the following positions to set which GPS accuracy metrics will be used to calculate the blending weight. Set to zero to disable and always used first GPS instance. 0 : Set to true to use speed accuracy 1 : Set to true to use horizontal position accuracy 2 : Set to true to use vertical position accuracy

SENS_GPS_TAU.name: SENS_GPS_TAU
SENS_GPS_TAU.long_desc: Sets the longest time constant that will be applied to the calculation of GPS position and height offsets used to correct data from multiple GPS data for steady state position differences.

SENS_GPS_PRIME.name: SENS_GPS_PRIME
SENS_GPS_PRIME.long_desc: When no blending is active, this defines the preferred GPS receiver instance. The GPS selection logic waits until the primary receiver is available to send data to the EKF even if a secondary instance is already available. The secondary instance is then only used if the primary one times out.  To have an equal priority of all the instances, set this parameter to -1 and the best receiver will be used.  This parameter has no effect if blending is active.

IMU_INTEG_RATE.name: IMU_INTEG_RATE
IMU_INTEG_RATE.long_desc: The rate at which raw IMU data is integrated to produce delta angles and delta velocities. Recommended to set this to a multiple of the estimator update period (currently 10 ms for ekf2).

SENS_IMU_AUTOCAL.name: SENS_IMU_AUTOCAL
SENS_IMU_AUTOCAL.long_desc: Automatically initialize IMU (accel/gyro) calibration from bias estimates if available.

SENS_IMU_CLPNOTI.name: SENS_IMU_CLPNOTI
SENS_IMU_CLPNOTI.long_desc: Notify the user if the IMU is clipping

SIM_BAT_ENABLE.name: SIM_BAT_ENABLE
SIM_BAT_ENABLE.long_desc: Enable or disable the internal battery simulation. This is useful when the battery is simulated externally and interfaced with PX4 through MAVLink for example.

SIM_BAT_MIN_PCT.name: SIM_BAT_MIN_PCT
SIM_BAT_MIN_PCT.long_desc: Can be used to alter the battery level during SITL- or HITL-simulation on the fly. Particularly useful for testing different low-battery behaviour.

SIM_AGP_FAIL.name: SIM_AGP_FAIL
SIM_AGP_FAIL.long_desc: Stuck: freeze the measurement to the current location Drift: add a linearly growing bias to the sensor data

SIM_ARSPD_FAIL.name: SIM_ARSPD_FAIL
SIM_ARSPD_FAIL.short_desc: Dynamically simulate failure of airspeed sensor instance

SIM_GPS_USED.name: SIM_GPS_USED
SIM_GPS_USED.short_desc: simulated GPS number of satellites used

SIH_MASS.name: SIH_MASS
SIH_MASS.long_desc: This value can be measured by weighting the quad on a scale.

SIH_IXX.name: SIH_IXX
SIH_IXX.long_desc: The inertia is a 3 by 3 symmetric matrix. It represents the difficulty of the vehicle to modify its angular rate.

SIH_IYY.name: SIH_IYY
SIH_IYY.long_desc: The inertia is a 3 by 3 symmetric matrix. It represents the difficulty of the vehicle to modify its angular rate.

SIH_IZZ.name: SIH_IZZ
SIH_IZZ.long_desc: The inertia is a 3 by 3 symmetric matrix. It represents the difficulty of the vehicle to modify its angular rate.

SIH_IXY.name: SIH_IXY
SIH_IXY.long_desc: The inertia is a 3 by 3 symmetric matrix. This value can be set to 0 for a quad symmetric about its center of mass.

SIH_IXZ.name: SIH_IXZ
SIH_IXZ.long_desc: The inertia is a 3 by 3 symmetric matrix. This value can be set to 0 for a quad symmetric about its center of mass.

SIH_IYZ.name: SIH_IYZ
SIH_IYZ.long_desc: The inertia is a 3 by 3 symmetric matrix. This value can be set to 0 for a quad symmetric about its center of mass.

SIH_T_MAX.name: SIH_T_MAX
SIH_T_MAX.long_desc: This is the maximum force delivered by one propeller when the motor is running at full speed.  This value is usually about 5 times the mass of the quadrotor.

SIH_Q_MAX.name: SIH_Q_MAX
SIH_Q_MAX.long_desc: This is the maximum torque delivered by one propeller when the motor is running at full speed.  This value is usually about few percent of the maximum thrust force.

SIH_L_ROLL.name: SIH_L_ROLL
SIH_L_ROLL.long_desc: This is the arm length generating the rolling moment  This value can be measured with a ruler. This corresponds to half the distance between the left and right motors.

SIH_L_PITCH.name: SIH_L_PITCH
SIH_L_PITCH.long_desc: This is the arm length generating the pitching moment  This value can be measured with a ruler. This corresponds to half the distance between the front and rear motors.

SIH_KDV.name: SIH_KDV
SIH_KDV.long_desc: Physical coefficient representing the friction with air particules. The greater this value, the slower the quad will move.  Drag force function of velocity: D=-KDV*V. The maximum freefall velocity can be computed as V=10*MASS/KDV [m/s]

SIH_KDW.name: SIH_KDW
SIH_KDW.long_desc: Physical coefficient representing the friction with air particules during rotations. The greater this value, the slower the quad will rotate.  Aerodynamic moment function of body rate: Ma=-KDW*W_B. This value can be set to 0 if unknown.

SIH_LOC_LAT0.name: SIH_LOC_LAT0
SIH_LOC_LAT0.long_desc: This value represents the North-South location on Earth where the simulation begins.  LAT0, LON0, H0, MU_X, MU_Y, and MU_Z should ideally be consistent among each others to represent a physical ground location on Earth.

SIH_LOC_LON0.name: SIH_LOC_LON0
SIH_LOC_LON0.long_desc: This value represents the East-West location on Earth where the simulation begins.  LAT0, LON0, H0, MU_X, MU_Y, and MU_Z should ideally be consistent among each others to represent a physical ground location on Earth.

SIH_LOC_H0.name: SIH_LOC_H0
SIH_LOC_H0.long_desc: This value represents the Above Mean Sea Level (AMSL) altitude where the simulation begins.  If using FlightGear as a visual animation, this value can be tweaked such that the vehicle lies on the ground at takeoff.  LAT0, LON0, H0, MU_X, MU_Y, and MU_Z should ideally be consistent among each others to represent a physical ground location on Earth.

SIH_DISTSNSR_OVR.name: SIH_DISTSNSR_OVR
SIH_DISTSNSR_OVR.short_desc: if >= 0 the distance sensor measures will be overridden by this value
SIH_DISTSNSR_OVR.long_desc: Absolute value superior to 10000 will disable distance sensor

SIH_T_TAU.name: SIH_T_TAU
SIH_T_TAU.long_desc: the time taken for the thruster to step from 0 to 100% should be about 4 times tau

TC_A0_ID.name: TC_A0_ID
TC_A0_ID.short_desc: ID of Accelerometer that the calibration is for.

TC_A0_X3_0.name: TC_A0_X3_0
TC_A0_X3_0.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^3 polynomial coefficient - X axis.

TC_A0_X3_1.name: TC_A0_X3_1
TC_A0_X3_1.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^3 polynomial coefficient - Y axis.

TC_A0_X3_2.name: TC_A0_X3_2
TC_A0_X3_2.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^3 polynomial coefficient - Z axis.

TC_A0_X2_0.name: TC_A0_X2_0
TC_A0_X2_0.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^2 polynomial coefficient - X axis.

TC_A0_X2_1.name: TC_A0_X2_1
TC_A0_X2_1.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^2 polynomial coefficient - Y axis.

TC_A0_X2_2.name: TC_A0_X2_2
TC_A0_X2_2.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^2 polynomial coefficient - Z axis.

TC_A0_X1_0.name: TC_A0_X1_0
TC_A0_X1_0.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^1 polynomial coefficient - X axis.

TC_A0_X1_1.name: TC_A0_X1_1
TC_A0_X1_1.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^1 polynomial coefficient - Y axis.

TC_A0_X1_2.name: TC_A0_X1_2
TC_A0_X1_2.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^1 polynomial coefficient - Z axis.

TC_A0_X0_0.name: TC_A0_X0_0
TC_A0_X0_0.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^0 polynomial coefficient - X axis.

TC_A0_X0_1.name: TC_A0_X0_1
TC_A0_X0_1.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^0 polynomial coefficient - Y axis.

TC_A0_X0_2.name: TC_A0_X0_2
TC_A0_X0_2.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^0 polynomial coefficient - Z axis.

TC_A1_ID.name: TC_A1_ID
TC_A1_ID.short_desc: ID of Accelerometer that the calibration is for.

TC_A1_X3_0.name: TC_A1_X3_0
TC_A1_X3_0.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^3 polynomial coefficient - X axis.

TC_A1_X3_1.name: TC_A1_X3_1
TC_A1_X3_1.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^3 polynomial coefficient - Y axis.

TC_A1_X3_2.name: TC_A1_X3_2
TC_A1_X3_2.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^3 polynomial coefficient - Z axis.

TC_A1_X2_0.name: TC_A1_X2_0
TC_A1_X2_0.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^2 polynomial coefficient - X axis.

TC_A1_X2_1.name: TC_A1_X2_1
TC_A1_X2_1.short_desc: Accelerometer offset temperature ^2 polynomial coefficient - Y axis.

TC_A1_X2_2.name: TC_A1_X2_2
