VT_FWD_THRUST_EN.name: VT_FWD_THRUST_EN
VT_FWD_THRUST_EN.short_desc: Use fixed-wing actuation in hover to accelerate forward
VT_FWD_THRUST_EN.long_desc: This feature can be used to avoid the plane having to pitch nose down in order to move forward. Prevents large, negative lift from pitching nose down into wind. Fixed-wing forward actuators refers to puller/pusher (standard VTOL), or forward-tilt (tiltrotor VTOL). Only active if demanded down pitch is below VT_PITCH_MIN. Use VT_FWD_THRUST_SC to tune it. Descend mode is treated as Landing too.  Only active (if enabled) in Altitude, Position and Auto modes, not in Stabilized.

VT_FWD_THRUST_SC.name: VT_FWD_THRUST_SC
VT_FWD_THRUST_SC.short_desc: Fixed-wing actuation thrust scale for hover forward flight
VT_FWD_THRUST_SC.long_desc: Scale applied to the demanded down-pitch to get the fixed-wing forward actuation in hover mode. Enabled via VT_FWD_THRUST_EN.

VT_B_TRANS_RAMP.name: VT_B_TRANS_RAMP
VT_B_TRANS_RAMP.short_desc: Back transition MC motor ramp up time
VT_B_TRANS_RAMP.long_desc: This sets the duration during which the MC motors ramp up to the commanded thrust during the back transition stage.

VT_PSHER_SLEW.name: VT_PSHER_SLEW
VT_PSHER_SLEW.short_desc: Pusher throttle ramp up slew rate
VT_PSHER_SLEW.long_desc: Defines the slew rate of the puller/pusher throttle during transitions. Zero will deactivate the slew rate limiting and thus produce an instant throttle rise to the transition throttle VT_F_TRANS_THR.

VT_TILT_TRANS.name: VT_TILT_TRANS
VT_TILT_TRANS.short_desc: Normalized tilt in transition to FW

VT_TRANS_P2_DUR.name: VT_TRANS_P2_DUR
VT_TRANS_P2_DUR.long_desc: Time in seconds it takes to tilt form VT_TILT_TRANS to VT_TILT_FW.

VT_BT_TILT_DUR.name: VT_BT_TILT_DUR
VT_BT_TILT_DUR.short_desc: Duration motor tilt up in backtransition
VT_BT_TILT_DUR.long_desc: Time in seconds it takes to tilt form VT_TILT_FW to VT_TILT_MC.

VT_ELEV_MC_LOCK.name: VT_ELEV_MC_LOCK
VT_ELEV_MC_LOCK.long_desc: If set to 1 the control surfaces are locked at the disarmed value in multicopter mode.

VT_F_TRANS_DUR.name: VT_F_TRANS_DUR
VT_F_TRANS_DUR.long_desc: Time in seconds used for a transition

VT_B_TRANS_DUR.name: VT_B_TRANS_DUR
VT_B_TRANS_DUR.short_desc: Maximum duration of a back transition
VT_B_TRANS_DUR.long_desc: Transition is also declared over if the groundspeed drops below MPC_XY_CRUISE.

VT_F_TRANS_THR.name: VT_F_TRANS_THR
VT_F_TRANS_THR.short_desc: Target throttle value for the transition to fixed-wing flight.

VT_B_DEC_MSS.name: VT_B_DEC_MSS
VT_B_DEC_MSS.long_desc: Used to calculate back transition distance in an auto mode. For standard vtol and tiltrotors a controller is used to track this value during the transition.

VT_ARSP_BLEND.name: VT_ARSP_BLEND
VT_ARSP_BLEND.long_desc: Airspeed at which we can start blending both fw and mc controls. Set to 0 to disable.

VT_ARSP_TRANS.name: VT_ARSP_TRANS
VT_ARSP_TRANS.long_desc: Airspeed at which we can switch to fw mode

VT_TRANS_TIMEOUT.name: VT_TRANS_TIMEOUT
VT_TRANS_TIMEOUT.long_desc: Time in seconds after which transition will be cancelled. Disabled if set to 0.

VT_TRANS_MIN_TM.name: VT_TRANS_MIN_TM
VT_TRANS_MIN_TM.long_desc: Minimum time in seconds for front transition.

VT_FW_MIN_ALT.name: VT_FW_MIN_ALT
VT_FW_MIN_ALT.long_desc: Minimum altitude for fixed-wing flight. When the vehicle is in fixed-wing mode and the altitude drops below this altitude (relative altitude above local origin), it will instantly switch back to MC mode and execute behavior defined in COM_QC_ACT.

VT_QC_ALT_LOSS.name: VT_QC_ALT_LOSS
VT_QC_ALT_LOSS.long_desc: Altitude error threshold for quad-chute triggering during fixed-wing flight. The check is only active if altitude is controlled and the vehicle is below the current altitude reference. The altitude error is relative to the highest altitude the vehicle has achieved since it has flown below the current altitude reference.  Set to 0 do disable.

VT_QC_T_ALT_LOSS.name: VT_QC_T_ALT_LOSS
VT_QC_T_ALT_LOSS.long_desc: Altitude loss threshold for quad-chute triggering during VTOL transition to fixed-wing flight in altitude-controlled flight modes. Active until 5s after completing transition to fixed-wing. If the current altitude is more than this value below the altitude at the beginning of the transition, it will instantly switch back to MC mode and execute behavior defined in COM_QC_ACT.  Set to 0 do disable this threshold.

VT_FW_QC_P.name: VT_FW_QC_P
VT_FW_QC_P.long_desc: Absolute pitch threshold for quad-chute triggering in FW mode. Above this the vehicle will transition back to MC mode and execute behavior defined in COM_QC_ACT. Set to 0 do disable this threshold.

VT_FW_QC_R.name: VT_FW_QC_R
VT_FW_QC_R.long_desc: Absolute roll threshold for quad-chute triggering in FW mode. Above this the vehicle will transition back to MC mode and execute behavior defined in COM_QC_ACT. Set to 0 do disable this threshold.

VT_FW_QC_HMAX.name: VT_FW_QC_HMAX
VT_FW_QC_HMAX.long_desc: Maximum height above the ground (if available, otherwise above Home if available, otherwise above the local origin) where triggering a quad-chute is possible. At high altitudes there is a big risk to deplete the battery and therefore crash if quad-chuting there.

VT_F_TR_OL_TM.name: VT_F_TR_OL_TM
VT_F_TR_OL_TM.long_desc: The duration of the front transition when there is no airspeed feedback available.

VT_FW_DIFTHR_EN.name: VT_FW_DIFTHR_EN
VT_FW_DIFTHR_EN.long_desc: Enable differential thrust seperately for roll, pitch, yaw in forward (fixed-wing) mode. The effectiveness of differential thrust around the corresponding axis can be tuned by setting VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_R / VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_P / VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_Y.

VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_R.name: VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_R
VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_R.short_desc: Roll differential thrust factor in forward flight
VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_R.long_desc: Differential thrust in forward flight is enabled via VT_FW_DIFTHR_EN.

VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_P.name: VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_P
VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_P.short_desc: Pitch differential thrust factor in forward flight
VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_P.long_desc: Differential thrust in forward flight is enabled via VT_FW_DIFTHR_EN.

VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_Y.name: VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_Y
VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_Y.short_desc: Yaw differential thrust factor in forward flight
VT_FW_DIFTHR_S_Y.long_desc: Differential thrust in forward flight is enabled via VT_FW_DIFTHR_EN.

VT_B_DEC_I.name: VT_B_DEC_I
VT_B_DEC_I.short_desc: Backtransition deceleration setpoint to pitch I gain.

VT_PITCH_MIN.name: VT_PITCH_MIN
VT_PITCH_MIN.long_desc: Any pitch setpoint below this value is translated to a forward force by the fixed-wing forward actuation if VT_FWD_TRHUST_EN is set.

VT_LND_PITCH_MIN.name: VT_LND_PITCH_MIN
VT_LND_PITCH_MIN.short_desc: Minimum pitch angle during hover landing.
VT_LND_PITCH_MIN.long_desc: Overrides VT_PITCH_MIN when the vehicle is in LAND mode (hovering). During landing it can be beneficial to reduce the pitch angle to reduce the generated lift in head wind.
